title: grilled parm potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Wrap securely in heavy-duty foil.
Grill over medium coals 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender, turning occasionally.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Add hamburger, green pepper and onion. Brown.
Mix other ingredients and add to meat.
Cook in crock-pot for 2 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer macaroni and cheddar cheese in 2 qt. baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Combine tomatoes and seasonings in bowl; mix well.
Pour tomato mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Bake covered at 400° for 45 minutes.
Add mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer.

title: schwabisches sauerkraut(swabian style kraut)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with warm water, drain well.
Saute the apples and onion in butter or pork fat until soft.
Add juniper or caraway, sugar and the rinsed kraut.
Simmer, covered, 1/2 hour. Add potato, water or wine and salt.
Continue cooking until sauerkraut is tender to your taste (about 1 hour longer).
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplants.
Dip eggplants in egg mixture; then coat with bread crumbs.
Saute in olive oil.
Layer in a casserole dish:

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix peanut butter, dry milk powder, honey and vanilla.
Stir in enough Rice Krispies to make stiff consistency. Roll into balls (can hide nuts, raisins or chocolate chips inside).
Roll in wheat germ or toasted coconut.
Chill and enjoy!

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Salt and pepper; roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
When brown, add other ingredients. Simmer on low until tender.
Great with baked potato.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until set and brown.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add fruit cocktail and stir in.
Add all other ingredients, except nuts, and stir well.
Pour into greased 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook diced up boneless chicken.
Add onions and celery.
Add chilies.
Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Heat.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder soda and salt.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour mixture. Gradually beat in milk and spices.
Add persimmon pulp last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in glass baking dish.
Let cool briefly and serve warm, topping with Cool Whip.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Crumble enough chips to cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch ovenproof casserole dish. Saut meat, onion and taco mix until cooked, but not brown. Drain liquid. Spread mixture over chips. Next, spread beans over meat mixture, then 1 cup of cheese over beans. Spread soup over cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes over soup, spreading evenly. Top off with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until nice and bubbly. Serve with large green salad and steamed corn tortillas. Serve with piquante to be used as desired. Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and evaporated milk until stiff.
Pat half of the mixture into a well-greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: african stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat slices and onions in oil or butter.
Add beans sprouts or cucumber chunks.
Add pineapple chunks and mandarin orange segments.
Set aside, covered.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Pour stir-fry over cooked rice.
Sprinkle with chopped cashews, small tomato chunks and chopped green chives.
Serve with soy sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean and vegetable soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook salt pork in a small skillet over very low heat until it gives up its fat.
Strain the fat and put 2 tablespoons in a large soup pot.
Set aside the crisp scraps. Heat the fat and add the garlic, onion, carrots and squash.
Cook over low heat, adding a little more fat or vegetable oil, if necessary for about 15 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes, and beans and reserved liquid.
Partially cover and simmer for about 1 hour until the beans and the vegetables are tender.
Add the cabbage and cook 15 minutes.
Add the pork scraps and salt and pepper to taste.
Reheat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Cut into bite size and arrange in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with almonds.
Sprinkle over chicken; pour melted margarine evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good served over rice or noodles.
Real rich tasting.

title: pork roast barbecue
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook 6 to 8 hours (high).
Drain off liquid, then add about 1/2 bottle barbecue sauce and let cook another couple of hours (on high for about 30 minutes, then on low for remainder of cooking time).

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix flour, baking powder, and sugar together.
Using a fork, cut in the crisco, add cheese and stir in buttermilk all at one time until blended.
Roll out biscuits (or drop by tablespoonsful) on a well-greased baking pan. Bake for 12-15 minutes.

title: paradise lemonade
directions: Combine lemonade with one can water.
Add apricot and pineapple.
Add ice and ginger ale.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into patties and fry in oil or bake on a Pam-sprayed cookie sheet until browned.

title: hot crab meat appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into small ovenproof dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: "smashed peanuts"-kindergarten p b j
directions: Henry Says To:
Take butter knife and put peanut butter on bread.
Spread jelly on the other.
Put it together.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: lemon lush or 3 layer lemon dessert
directions: Blend together flour, oleo and pecans; bake at 350° until very light brown. Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Spread over crust. Prepare instant lemon pudding with milk. Mix until slightly thickened and spread over cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugars, milk and margarine.
Bring mixture to boil and boil for 1 minute.

title: mermaid salad
directions: Boil noodles according to package.
Rinse and set aside.
In a large bowl, whisk together remaining ingredients.
Add cooked macaroni. Chill overnight.
Double for a crowd.

title: chicken noodle casserole(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together in a large container.
Place in a large casserole sprayed with Pam, 1/2 of the mixture.
The other 1/2 can be saved for a later date; this freezes well.
Dot top of casserole with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° (until hot and cheese is melted).
This can also be baked in the microwave on High with a lid on it.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of mushroom soup

title: carol's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain well. Combine all other ingredients.
Put into greased casserole dish. Cover with Durkee dried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: melted onion potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place them in the middle of 16-inch square of aluminum foil.
Dice onion and put over potatoes.
Cover with butter.
Fold foil over top and sides.
Carefully seal all openings and bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.
Top with sprinkling of Parmesan cheese or garnish with parsley if desired.
Serves 4.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Puree tomatoes in electric blender; mix in seasonings.
Transfer chicken to a shallow baking dish; pour tomato sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; place Mozzarella cheese on chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: santa snacks
directions: Mix melted butter, cracker crumbs and coconut in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press lightly.
Cover with layer of chocolate pieces.
Sprinkle layer of chopped nuts; drizzle condensed milk evenly over surface.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put cut-up pieces of chicken into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour salad dressing over chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, turning chicken once.

title: deluxe hash browns
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain well.
In a large bowl, shred potatoes.
Stir in all other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by 1/3 cup into hot bacon grease.
With a turner, press into 3-inch patties.
Fry for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown, turning once.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place artichokes in bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish; spread a layer of crabmeat.
Add a layer of sauteed mushrooms.
Melt butter in a saucepan; add flour, cream, salt, Worcestershire sauce, sherry, paprika, cayenne pepper and pepper.
Stir well after each addition to form a smooth sauce. Pour sauce over artichoke-crab layer and spread with cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp party ring
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup consomme.
Heat remaining consomme; add softened gelatin to dissolve.
Cool.
In a bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Add cooled consomme and all other ingredients.
Place in a lightly greased 2-quart ring mold or fish mold.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce with French dressing.
Can be prepared the day before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls in a 12 x 17-inch pan.
Let cool.
Spread with mixture of Ranch dry mix, cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and Tabasco sauce.
Top with chopped vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, fresh mushrooms, green peppers, shredded cheese and bacon bits; whatever you want can be put on it.

title: chocolate chips cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully. Fill cupcakes cups half full. Bake in moderate oven (350°) 20 to 30 minutes. No frosting needed.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Cut up chicken and place in a 3-quart casserole.
Reserve stock.
Slice eggs on top of chicken.
Mix soup and two cups stock and pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook
the
first
vegetables,
each	separately,
in boiling salted water until just tender.
Rinse in cold running water
until
chilled.
Drain well.
It is very important that the vegetables remain crisp.
This may be done well in advance of preparing
the
pasta,
refrigerating
the	vegetables
in plastic bags.
Place
the	cooked vegetables in a bowl.
In a medium-sized skillet, saute mushrooms, scallions and garlic in 2 tablespoons
butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to the bowl of vegetables,
along	with parsley, basil and red pepper flakes. In a
large
pan
or
Dutch
oven,
melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add chicken broth, cream, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir with
a whisk
until smooth, but do not boil.
Add vegetables only	to heat
through, then cooked pasta.
Check seasonings. Serve immediately,
dividing
among heated plates with sprinklings of toasted pine nuts on top.
Pass extra cheese.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Spread bread cubes in an 8-inch round dish.
Cover with brown sugar.
Measure milk into 1-quart measuring cup.
Add butter and microwave until butter melts.
Quickly stir in egg mixture; pour over bread cubes.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure corn flakes.
Crush to 3/4 cup. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Measure butter and sugar into large bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and orange peel.
Beat well.
Stir in juice.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° about 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool before slicing.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add half and half and cream; beat.
Add the rest of the ingredients; beat.
Pour into a quiche dish or deep pie plate.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes, or until a knife blade comes out clean.
This recipe may be halved or doubled.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a large cookie sheet. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 1 inch apart, on prepared cookie sheet, pressing down ends of coconut with the back of a spoon.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: mantel beef
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain grease. Add manwich and rotel; heat thoroughly. Add cheese, stir till melted. Stir in macaroni. You can add a can of pork and beans, or a can of whole kernel corn or both. Serves 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add taco seasoning and water; stir. Then add soup and drained corn; stir well.
Pour this on top of Doritos that have been spread in bottom of dish.
Top with cheese (more cheese the better).
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: healthy egg nog
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together well.
Serve chilled and garnish with grated orange rind and/or cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl except the soup and milk.
Form in 2-inch balls and brown.
In a 3-quart saucepan, blend the mushroom soup and milk until creamy on low heat.
Add meatballs and simmer in covered pot for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Combine ice cream topping and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Cover with candy chips and chopped walnuts.

title: prune whip pie
directions: Add salt to room temperature egg whites.
Beat until stiff. Beat in sugar gradually.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in prunes and nuts.
Pile lightly into baked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender on high for 10 min.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° for 40 min until slightly brown.

title: skillet corn
directions: Prepare corn.
Cut enough kernels from corn to measure 2 cups. Cook and stir in all ingredients in skillet over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Cook over low heat until corn is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix in large bowl the flour, cocoa and sugar (dry ingredients). In small bowl, beat 2 egg yolks.
Add milk (both Pet and regular). Beat milk mixture with dry ingredients in large microwave bowl. Add 1 tablespoon white Karo syrup, 3 tablespoons melted butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat with mixer.
Put in microwave for 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
When it thickens, remove and beat 2 more minutes.
(Microwaves may vary in time.)
Pour in prepared crust.

title: dee dee's christmas fruit cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Beat with electric
mixer for 2 minutes. Sift 2 cups flour with baking powder, salt and spices. Stir into oil mixture alternately with juice or liquor.
Mix the other cup of flour with fruits and nuts.
Pour batter over fruit, mixing thoroughly.
Turn into 2 large loaf pans or large angel tin greased and lined with wax paper.
Place a pan of water on lower oven rack. Bake cake(s) at 275° in preheated oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
After baking, let stand 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool thoroughly on racks.
Glaze, if desired.
When cool, remove paper. Wrap in aluminum foil.
Store in cool place to ripen.
If desired, cakes can be wrapped in cloth dampened with brandy or wine. An hour or two before slicing, chill cake in the refrigerator.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add buttermilk.
Batter will be thin.
Drop by tablespoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: chewy homestead brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add alternately with chocolate mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan.
Cool in pan; frost, if desired.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Prepare quick meat broth and set aside.
Dice bacon and place into pot.
Cook slowly, stirring and turning frequently, until bacon is lightly brown. Remove bacon with slotted spoon from saucepot to small bowl and set aside.
Add chopped onion to bacon fat and cook over medium heat until onion is almost tender.
Remove onion with slotted spoon to bowl containing bacon and set aside.
Add meat to bacon fat and slowly brown on all sides, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle evenly over meat a mixture of paprika, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Stir in bacon-onion mixture.
Slowly pour in meat broth and wine.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat with slotted spoon to thicken liquid.
Mix cornstarch with about 1/2 cup water and add to liquid.
Let boil for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add meat.
Serve over noodles.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except Swiss cheese and mix well until smooth.
Spread into a 1 1/2-inch deep 11 x 7-inch glass casserole baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top, put back into oven and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch cheesecake.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together until cheese is melted.
Put in an oven dish. Take some crumbled potato chips and put on top of cheese and vegetables.
Heat in oven until chips are light brown.

title: pie dough mix
directions: Mix well with hands until crumbly.
Store in airtight container until you are ready to make pie.
Use 2 heaping cups mix with scant 1/3 cup milk.
Mix with fork or pastry blender and roll out.

title: caramel mocha sundaes
directions: Mix coffee and brown sugar in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Continue cooking until mixture begins to thicken and becomes syrupy, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Mix in vanilla and brandy (if used).
Cool to room temperature. Pour syrup over ice cream in 4 sundae dishes, reserving a little. Dollop or pipe whipping cream over each serving.
Drizzle with remaining syrup.
Sprinkle with any topping you please.
Serve immediately.

title: italian bean and sausage soup
directions: Place sausage in 3-quart microwavable casserole; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Drain drippings; set sausage aside.
Using same casserole, combine beef broth, tomatoes, green pepper, onion, garlic and seasonings.
Cover; microwave on High for 15 to 17 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Add reserved sausage and beans.
Then microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add parsley.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Mix together water and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in honey, salt and oil.
Add 3 cups of flour; beat until smooth.
Add last 3 cups of flour and knead until barely firm.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and stretch to cover bottom and 1 1/2 inch sides of a large iron frying pan.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Cover with favorite toppings.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes. Best when baked in a wood stove.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oil in skillet.
Chop chiles after removing seeds. Saute with minced garlic in oil.
Drain and break up tomatoes. Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
To chiles and garlic, add tomatoes, onions, 1 teaspoon of salt, oregano and reserved tomato liquid. Simmer, uncovered, until thick, about 30 minutes.
Remove and set aside.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Add boiling water to oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes. Add sugar and margarine until it melts.
Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add 1/2 chocolate chips.
Pour into pan. Add rest of nuts and chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Make white sauce with milk, flour, cheese and butter.
Pour over cauliflower.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Combine with finely crushed crackers and nuts.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, set aside.
Sift together remaining ingredients and then add to first mixture. Roll into balls the size of walnuts and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Makes 3-4 dozen.

title: creamy italian-style salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill. Yields 1 cup.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Soften margarine.
Add peanut butter and sugar; mix well. (May seem impossible, but keep mixing with hands as if kneading dough.)
Roll into small balls and refrigerate on cookie sheets.

title: grandma's molasses cremes
directions: Cream together brown sugar, butter, shortening and eggs.
In another bowl, add molasses to boiling water, then mix in with creamed mixture.
Add all dry ingredients to creamed mixture and stir thoroughly until blended and smooth.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 15 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes (do not overbake).
While still warm, frost with thin white icing. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt margarine and then add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add 2 slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Blend.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Mix well. Spread in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *Can use Bisquick, etc. for biscuits.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Shred lettuce.
Combine with peas, onion, mayonnaise, bacon, cheese and salt.
Toss until ingredients are mixed well.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, margarine, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour first 2 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Add pecan bits, if you wish.
Cut pats of butter and put all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Whip cream cheese; fry and crumble bacon.
Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix cream cheese and bacon crumbs.
Spoon into mushroom caps.
Brush outside of mushrooms with melted margarine and set on cookie sheet.
Broil 5 minutes or until top is slightly brown.

title: oatmeal refrigerator crisps
directions: Mix and form into roll.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake in hot oven.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Place the candy bar, marshmallows and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream: pour into crust.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line 2 loaf pans with waxed paper.
Blend eggs and milk, then stir in Bisquick and cheese. Blend well.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool 5 minutes and slice 1/2-inch thick.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Blend peppers to a fine mush.
Put in heavy saucepan and add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil vigorously while stirring, 2 minutes.
Set aside; skim.
Add pectin and pour into sterilized jars.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix all together, refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving. Serving tip:
Serve in new pottery, flower pot, top with fresh mint leaves or a few silk flower stems.
Have fun!
Enjoy!

title: sputniks
directions: Combine peanut butter and chips and microwave 2 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Add chow mein noodles and nuts and drop on wax paper and refrigerate until set.

title: emery's ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken until tender, dice chicken.
Add soup and broth, simmer until creamy.
In a 9 by 13 in. casserole dish cover bottom with mixture.
Place 2 tortillas on top, if they are slightly overlapping it's okay.
Next start layering with tortillas, chicken, then cheese.
Repeat until tortillas are gone. End with sauce, leave off cheese and bake 25 min. at 350°.
Top with cheese and let stand 10 minutes, cut and serve. To add a bite you can add green chilies when you simmer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop all ingredients fine and pour on sauce; toss well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Cook noodles al dente.
Steam broccoli until tender.
Cook chicken until tender, then debone; cut up in bite size pieces and reserve stock.
Combine last 5 ingredients for sauce.
Using 3 (8-inch) square foil pans, layer noodles, broccoli, chicken and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Toward end of cooking (when bubbly) sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Freezes well:
bake foil wrapped casserole for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chunky chicken nachos
directions: Chop chicken in small cubes and fry in oil. Mix all canned ingredients in a deep pan. Stir in chicken and heat until warm. Spoon over tortilla chips or use as a dip.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring milk, cocoa and sugar to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Add 1 stick butter and the peanut butter. Stir until melted.
Add the oatmeal. Stir and drop onto wax paper to cool.

title: jam dough frosting for jam cake
directions: Cook until thick.
Spread on cool cake.

title: homemade oreo cookies
directions: Blend together. Roll into balls the size of quarters.
Bake 9 minutes at 350°.

title: baby tea loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add squash.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Reserve 1/4 cup flour mixture and work it into dates and nuts.
Add flour mixture to squash mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts into batter.
Turn batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with 1 1/2 cups salt. Let set overnight. Drain. Tie all spices in cloth bag and add to vinegar and simmer 30 minutes. Add all other ingredients. Simmer until hot. Remove spiced bag. Pack hot Chow Chow into jars and seal at once.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Put crushed walnuts on the bottom of a greased Bundt pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: trout almondine
directions: Combine butter and almonds in a 2-cup glass measure. Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until almonds are lightly browned, stirring twice.

title: cabbage crunch
directions: Toast sesame
seed
and
almonds about 10 minutes.
Mix cabbage and onion.
Crumble noodles in with nuts and seed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Quick and easy.
Combine the ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers and drain well.
Use juices, enough to make 2 cups (can use blender and blend peppers, use pulp and juice).

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Make dressing at least 1 hour ahead so spices can blend (very runny, so toss just before serving).

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Layer chili, onion, cheese and Fritos in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine and heat in saucepan over very low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: southwest beef rolls
directions: Moisten stuffing with 3 tablespoons hot water.
Spread stuffing onto top of each steak.
Roll up; fasten each with toothpick.
Brown in nonstick skillet over medium heat about 6 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer 20 to 30 minutes until tender.

title: english rocks
directions: Chop fruits and nuts; mix all ingredients well and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: apple crumble
directions: Sift flour with sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Cut in peanut butter and butter until mixture is crumbly; add peanuts.
Peel apples; slice thin and place in well-greased baking dish (10 x 7 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle peanut butter mixture evenly over top of apples.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, then increase temperature to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until browned.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: dip (for rye bread)
directions: Scoop out center of rye bread.
Mix together the first 8 ingredients and fill center of rye bread.
Arrange slices from 1 party stick dark rye and 1 party stick light rye around the edges.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients; turn into pie shell.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Chop salmon fine. Add salt, pepper, crumbs and lemon juice. Add beaten egg yolks, mixing thoroughly, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Place in greased custard cups.
Set in pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes. Unmold on a hot platter. Garnish each with a sprig of parsley and serve with a sauce.
Serves 6.

title: dessert bars
directions: Melt the oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer the ingredients as given; except milk.
Then pour milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: simplified blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and milk mixture (do not beat) until all is moist.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill 12 greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool slightly.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: homemade brown sugar
directions: Blend together thoroughly and keep in airtight container.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until nearly done in boiling salted water. Peel them and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Grease a baking dish and place in alternating layers the sweet potatoes and apples.
(If the apples are not tart, sprinkle them with lemon juice.) Sprinkle the layers with brown sugar.
Dot them with 4 tablespoons butter.
Pour over them water or apple juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetable, soup, 1/2 C. of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of onions.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown beef, heat can of sauce with 1 can water.
After meat is brown, add a little of sauce, peppers and seasoning; simmer.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: aunt patsy's eggs
directions: Cook pork and place evenly in bottom of a 13x9-inch dish. Layer bread cubes on top of pork.
Mix together eggs, cheese, mustard and milk.
Add salt and pepper to season.
Pour mixture over bread and pork.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes, or until eggs are slightly brown on top.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and orange extract. Add flour and salt.
Mix and chill dough 10 minutes.
Pack into cookie gun and make desired shapes.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, saute beef cubes, onion and butter until meat is brown.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 hour until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms, sour cream and flour to meat mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes until sauce is thickened. Meanwhile, cook noodles; drain.
Pour meat mixture with noodles and mix well.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and soda in mixing bowl; add 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water; stir until thickens.
Add sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir; add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 32 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost if desired.

title: cold crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth, about 30 seconds. Serve with cucumbers, quartered lengthwise.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add milk to make gallon. Put in freezer and freeze until done.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar,
crumbs,
peanut butter and butter in a bowl until blended.
Put into
greased
x
9-inch pan and press into even layer.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Let stand 1/2 hour before cutting.

title: lemon icebox sandwiches
directions: Put a mixing bowl and beaters of mixer in freezer.
Put the milk in the refrigerator.
Put a layer of graham crackers in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch (1/4 sheet) cake pan.
Take the milk out of the refrigerator when chilled.
Put in chilled mixing bowl and beat on medium speed.
As you beat the milk, slowly add in the sugar, lemon and vanilla.
Blend all ingredients well, then pour the mixture over the graham crackers carefully.
Put another layer of graham crackers over the lemon mixture to make a sandwich.
Freeze at least 4 to 6 hours.
Cut in squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 12, depending on the size squares cut.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt, pepper, basil and parsley to taste.
Add rice.
When meat is cooled, add 5 eggs, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: zucchini pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Mix together the flour, soda, baking powder, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together, then add raisins and walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: lunch box cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Cream butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in oats and Raisin Bran. Drop by level tablespoon 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Let cool for 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.

title: grandmom kowki's cheese sauce
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over hot cooked vegetables.

title: blanched green salad
directions: Blanch lettuce with hot water (just wilt).
Serve with dressing.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion and pepperoni.
Drain grease and add spaghetti sauce and bell pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Prepare noodles in advance and add to casserole dish.
Pour sauce over noodles and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the sauce (as much as you like).
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cool until spreading consistency, beating occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups, enough for 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon of the flour with the salt; dredge the meat in mixture.
Heat skillet, then add 2 tablespoons of the butter.
When melted, add the sirloin strips and brown quickly, flipping meat on all sides.
Add mushroom slices, onion and garlic; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is barely tender. Remove the meat and mushrooms from the skillet.
Add the remaining butter to the pan drippings; when melted, blend in the remaining flour.
Add tomato paste.
Slowly pour in beef broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet.
This much can be done ahead of time, like the night before.
Stir in sour cream and sherry; heat briefly and serve.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Put blueberries in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add pineapple over blueberries.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Sprinkle cake mix on top and melt butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Blend together sugar, salt, sour cream, onions and vinegar. Stir in cucumbers.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: crispy chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and dash of salt.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil. Stir in cereals, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour; cut into bars.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cooking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.
Servings: 2.

title: beacon hill brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat. Stir constantly.
Cool.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl on high speed for 10 minutes.
Blend in chocolate on low speed.
Add flour, beating just to blend.
Stir in nuts. Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato onion bake
directions: Melt butter with onion soup mix.
Put 1/2 cup water in casserole.
Layer potatoes, alternately with onion soup and butter mixture.
End with mix on top.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery before mixing with other ingredients and putting into oblong Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until hot.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat 2 sticks margarine and sugar.
Add flour, pecans, 1/2 cup cocoa, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on top and return to warm oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until melted.
Mix powdered sugar, milk, 1/3 cup cocoa and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread on warm cake.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill overnight.
You can freeze in ring mold and slice to serve on lettuce.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put everything together.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In heavy pot, assemble all ingredients, but corn.
Cook, watch constantly to keep the stew from burning, about 2 hours or until thick.
Add corn during the last 1/2 hour.
If stew is too thin, thicken with some mashed potatoes; use potato flakes if you don't have leftover potatoes.

title: minted melon medley
directions: Combine sugar, water, lime juice, chopped mint, anise seed and salt.
Place in small saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Cover and steep 10 minutes.
Cool and then chill.
Place fruit in bowl and strain syrup over fruit to remove anise seed. Cover and chill 2 hours or until ready to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: no-fat pie crust
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, mix enough Grape-Nuts cereal with enough apple juice concentrate to shape in pie plate.
This is a great crust for a low-fat pumpkin pie or can be used for unbaked pies as well.

title: crispy belgian waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour onto hot Belgian waffle maker. Cook until golden brown.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour; fold in pecans.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with fingers.
Bake at 300° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure flour and resift with salt.
Add slowly to beaten eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Roll very thin in a rectangle shape on floured board.
Let dry 1/2 hour.
Slice noodles. Separate and dry completely.
(Good in soup or cook for use in casseroles.)

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil spaghetti; drain well.
While hot, add margarine, eggs and Parmesan cheese to spaghetti.
Mix well.
Brown beef; drain and add to spaghetti sauce.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, form spaghetti mixture into a crust.
Add cottage cheese on top of spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti sauce with meat over this.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle oregano over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: big batch cookies
directions: Combine oil,
eggs
and
vanilla
in a "big" bowl until well mixed.
Add sugars and mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to sugar mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in cereal and
remaining
ingredients.
Drop
by level tablespoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool slightly
on
cookie
sheet, then remove to wire rack.
Yields 9 dozen cookies.

title: play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan on medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes until forms a stiff ball stirring constantly. Take dough out of saucepan and let stand for 5 minutes.
Knead dough about 30 seconds or until well blended and smooth.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Will last about 6 weeks.

title: freezer sweet corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Simmer for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into large shallow container to cool.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon into freezer bags.
Freeze.

title: easy cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
While warm, stir in cake mix and oil; blend well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar together in a kettle.
Add milk and water.
Cook until thick.
Stir in butter.
Serve with breakfast.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream
sugar and butter thoroughly.
Beat in eggs.
Mix soda and
flour together and add to mixture along with buttermilk
and vanilla.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll out and cut. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: dark seduction cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Batter will be real thick. Fold in sour cream.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until cake pulls away from side of the pan and top is crusty.
Cool for 30 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Remove and let cool.
Remove bones; cut into bite size pieces and place in a casserole dish.
Combine soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add juice from pineapple. Chill until slightly thickened, then fold in remaining ingredients and chill until set.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, eggs and butter in blender.
Mix in pecan halves by hand.
Fill unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine all ingredients.
Chill. Shape on serving board to resemble pine cone, ball, log, etc. Garnish with chopped nuts or cracker crumbs.
Serve with fruit and/or crackers.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand overnight.
Will keep indefinitely if refrigerated.

title: fannie may cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add creme de menthe and mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cover with entire can of Hershey's chocolate fudge topping. Cover with Cool Whip to which 3 tablespoons creme de menthe has been added.
Refrigerate.
Great for holidays.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine, mix with pretzels and sugar.
Spread evenly in large Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix well with Cool Whip and sugar. Spread over cooled crust.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over jello and stir until dissolved.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Add strawberries, stir well into jello and pour over the cream cheese. Chill several hours before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Best served on Triscuit crackers!

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately until done; drain.
Saute onion in oleo; do not brown.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes a big casserole.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and cinnamon. Beat together butter and sugars at medium speed until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. At low speed, beat in flour mixture until blended. Fold in oats and chocolate chips. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two cookie sheets. Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Flatten each cookie. Bake cookies until lightly browned around edges. About 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In large bowl mix dry ingredients.
In a saucepan dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
When dissolved, pour into dry mixture; add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl, gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
In another bowl sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas and nuts, mixing gently just until blended.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool thoroughly then frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: breakfast on the go
directions: Beat eggs until foamy or whiz in the blender.
Add the soup and bacon.
Melt the margarine in a skillet and cook eggs as you would for scrambled eggs.
Spoon into warmed pitas and top with the shredded Cheddar.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Cook turkey in a medium saucepan until meat is brown, stirring to crumble the meat.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese melts.
To serve, transfer dip to a chafing dish and serve warm with tortilla chips. Makes 1 quart.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cream cheese topping while hot.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and mushrooms.
Remove spinach stems; slice mushrooms and onions.
Crumble Feta cheese and bacon.
Add all other ingredients except Feta cheese to the spinach.
Toss; then add Feta cheese; toss again.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt margarine; add cocoa and milk. Stir. Bring to a rolling boil and stir a little. Remove from heat and add sugar and vanilla. Then mix well and put on the cake.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line baking sheet with parchment paper; set aside.
In medium bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat on high speed until stiff; beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Add vanilla; fold in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave cookies in oven for 5 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: nana's mexican pizza(makes 3 large pizzas)
directions: Sprinkle over each pizza some pepper juice and the canned cayenne peppers.
Top each pizza with 6 canned cayenne peppers. Cut into slices.
Cook in a microwave for 2 to 3 minutes per slice or entire pizza in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: everyday green rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions using broth instead of water.
Saute vegetables in 1/4 cup margarine and stir into warm rice.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers).
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with crushed cheese crackers.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 2 or 3 hours before baking.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Put cake mix in large mixing bowl.
Add mandarin orange slices, eggs and oil and mix with electric mixer at high speed for 2 minutes.
Reduce speed to low and beat 1 minute more.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato sauce and beat in cream cheese with whisk until smooth.
Melt gelatine in water.
When soup mix cools, beat in gelatine and mayonnaise.
Stir in shrimp (drained, but not rinsed) and chopped vegetables.
Line mold with plastic wrap and pour mixture into it.
Chill.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare tube pan.
Cream the butter, Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Blend in raisins.
Add hot water and tomato soup.
Blend in flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add warm potatoes.
Mix well, add eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Dissolve yeast in water and add alternately with flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out on floured board about 3/4 inch thick.
Place in greased pan, let rise.
Cover with cream or undiluted canned milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and dot with cream or a thin glaze of cream and powdered sugar.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate several hours before serving.

title: hershey bars
directions: Spread half of the crushed wafers in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bar in double boiler.
Set aside.
Whip the cream and fold into melted Hershey bar.
Spread mixture over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Set overnight in refrigerator. Serves 9.

title: veal casserole
directions: Simmer veal, onion, celery and mushrooms until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add rice, soups, soy sauce and water.
Put in uncovered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Make as directed on box.
A 3 layer cake.
Cool cut into six layers.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Stir pepper into eggs.
Pour into hot nonstick skillet.
Cook until eggs begin to set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Cook until heated through, stirring gently.

title: yummy chips
directions: Cut pita so you have a top and a bottom.
Put on cookie sheet and cook at 425° until very crunchy.
Spray with butter spray and top with Molly McButter cheese or sour cream or whatever flavor you want.
Wait until cooled, then remove from cookie sheet and break into pieces.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place filling into prepared baking dish.
Top with crumbs. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 (10 ounce) entrees or 6 (7 ounce) side-dish servings.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine ingredients except onion and chicken in saucepan. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Arrange chicken in shallow open pan. Cover with onion and sauce.
Bake at 425°, basting frequently, about 20 minutes per side.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and milk together.
Stir until smooth.
Add the other ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: spanish tomatoes
directions: Break bread and place in a 9 x 10-inch baking dish. Cut onion and pepper into 1-inch slices.
Add sugar and bread to tomatoes. Pour over bread.
Shake Parmesan cheese on tomatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour, then stir. Bake 1/2 hour more.
Place 2 or 3 slices Mozzarella cheese and let melt.

title: fish cakes
directions: Remove the skin and bone and cream the fish with the sauce, seasoning, parsley and mashed potatoes. Spread the mixture on a plate.
Let it cool and divide it into 6 to 8 portions.
Shape into cakes using a little flour. Dip them in egg and crumbs.
Fry in hot margarine or Pam until golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: An Emergency Substitute for Sour Cream:
Combine 6 ounces cottage cheese and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Put in blender until smooth.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crunch up cookies in blender or by hand; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar until creamy.
Mix instant pudding with 2 3/4 cups milk, then fold in cream cheese mixture, then fold in 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Layer in flowerpot; start with cookies, mix, cookies and mix until you end up with cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving put a fake fern or flower in pot.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Cream together. Sift together the dry ingredients and mix all together except apples and nuts. Stir in apples and nuts. Bake in tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: dad's zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs before adding, then add vanilla, cinnamon, salt, flour and baking powder.
Beat until well mixed.
Add and stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
Chill until mixture starts to jell then add all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken, rice dish
directions: Oil bottom of large baking dish.
Spread rice over bottom. Pour in soup mixed with water.
Turn chicken over in oil.
Lay on top of rice and soup.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix white cake mix; add flour, cooking oil, water, eggs, jello and strawberries.
Bake in 2 cake pans at 350° until done.
Frost when cool.

title: texas party dip
directions: Saute ground beef until brown; drain well.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve in fondue dish or slow cooker to keep hot.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Keep on low heat.

title: chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown onion and green pepper in olive oil. Add ground round and brown.
Add soup and stir.
Season to taste with garlic powder, chili powder, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken with carrot, celery and onion.
Mix cream of celery soup, margarine and chicken broth together.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour soup mixture over.
(Cut the chicken up in small pieces.)
Mix the Bisquick and milk.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes (about 55 minutes).

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Roll in balls; dip in sugar.
Flatten with cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Drain juices from cherries and pineapple.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Make jello, using juice mixture and refrigerate.
Make small balls, using cream cheese and small amount of mayo and nuts. When jello starts to set, add fruit and cream cheese balls.

title: cherry coke jello
directions: Boil together the cherry pie filling and water.
Pour boiling water mixture over the Jell-O.
Stir to mix.
Add pineapple and nuts; stir again.
Stir in Coke and refrigerate to set.

title: "wacky cake"(cholesterol-free, no eggs cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease and dust with flour an 8-inch square cake pan.
Measure flour into sifter, add sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Sift into a heap into the center of the pan.
With a spoon, make 3 wells in the mound.
Into one, pour the oil; into the second, pour the vinegar, into the third, pour the vanilla.
Then pour cold water over it all.
Blend well with a fork.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes. Remove, finish cooling and frost if desired.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding with milk.
Pour pudding into dry cake mix.
Mix together well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle top of cake with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and rind, Eagle Brand
and egg yolks together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until peaks form.

title: chocolate cake(dump)
directions: Dump all ingredients together (except hot water) at one time before mixing.
Add water last and beat immediately.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 375°.

title: swedish sylta(traditional smorgasbord meat)
directions: Place meats in separate pans and cover with water.
Bring each to a boil, then
reduce heat to low setting.
When pork comes off bone easily, take both pans off heat.
(This may take 3 hours or longer.
Test pork by sticking with a fork and twisting.)
Allow to cool.

title: chocolate graham cracker cake(no cooking)
directions: Whip cream and vanilla together, then fold in sugar and syrup. Cover bottom of 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish with a layer of graham crackers.
Spread with whipped cream mixture.
Add second layer of crackers and spread as before.
Add third layer of crackers and cover with mixture.
Sprinkle with decors if you like.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: gringo burrito
directions: Spread butter or margarine in the center of aluminum foil where food will lay (you will do this for each dinner you prepare).
Next, peel and slice potatoes, onions and carrots.

title: fluffy butter icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until very thick.
Have cold, then add the butter (which is room temperature).
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy and smooth.
Put on cake.

title: best butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
In mixer, add flour mixture slowly with sugar mixture.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together; mix well and pour or brush on meat.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Mix in bowl the browned beef, tomato soup, Velveeta cheese, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread on French bread (cut in serving size).

title: pecan refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream
the
oleo
with
Sweet
'N Low brown sugar until light and
fluffy.
Add
the
egg and beat until light again. Fold flour
thoroughly
into creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Shape
into
long rolls 1 1/4-inch in diameter, wrap
in wax
paper and chill at least overnight.
The longer you chill, the better the cookies.
Slice the dough as thin as possible and bake
on greased baking sheet at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: katie's jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions, green pepper, ground beef and bacon.
Cook, stirring often until meat is browned.
Spoon off excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, measuring juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add the liquid, tomatoes, salt, sugar and thyme to mixture in skillet.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: tuna noodle casserole(this is a quick and easy dish to fix.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
(I have made this in a crock-pot.)

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, melted margarine and powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake mix and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Leave cake in pan.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini in butter and garlic.
Add salt, dill weed, and pepper.
Pour nuts in crust bottom; add zucchini, then eggs, cheese and parsley.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.

title: cashew ham bake
directions: Place ham slice on rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Spread marmalade over top and sprinkle with cashews. Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: mushroom florentine casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare Savory Crunch.
Mix spinach, soup and Worcestershire sauce in greased pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch). Arrange mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle Savory Crunch evenly over mushrooms.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: alabama mud cake
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While brownies are hot, pat marshmallows on top until covered.

title: butter rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place chopped pecans (and cherries if desired) in the bottom of pan.
Mix ingredients and spread over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Heat butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add hot milk or cream all at once, stirring constantly. Return to heat and stir until thickened.
Add catsup, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes.
Add shrimp. Bring to simmer.
Cook until shrimp turns pink.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry.
Serve with rice, salad and French bread.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan.
In a mixing bowl, put flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add the cooked mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix well with the mixer and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: winter cabbage salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil first 6 ingredients.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
In a
large bowl, combine cabbage, onions and peppers. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.
May be stored in refrigerator up to 3 months.

title: baby bourbon franks
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 1 hour, uncovered.
Add more bourbon if sauce becomes dry.
Serve in a chafing dish with picks.

title: mini cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over butter.
Put canned fruit on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nutty noodle dish
directions: Brown the beef, celery and onion.
Add the noodles, soup, water, cheese and salt to taste.
Put in casserole.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix the chow mein noodles and mixed nuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Serves 10.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Mix black cherry Jell-O with hot water.
Add crushed pineapple, strawberries (diced) and the chopped nuts to the Jell-O.
Congeal half of the mixture.
When Jell-O has become firm, gently cover with the sour cream, then pour remaining Jell-O mixture over the sour cream.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: brine
directions: Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
This amount is enough for one gallon.
Select cukes.
(I use pickling or straight 8's,
6 to 7-inches long or smaller.)
Leave 1/2-inch stem on.
Wash cukes with vegetable brush, making sure all foreign matter is removed.
Double check in 2nd bath.
(Cold water).
Have ready pickling spices, garlic and fresh dill.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight before using. Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: louise's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and partially boil the peppers for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: spinach taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Season with garlic, vinegar, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Add spinach.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni and drain. Brown turkey and add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and Sloppy Joe seasoning packet.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Beat egg, stir in milk and oil. Mix in remaining ingredients until flour is just moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Add 1 1/2 cup blueberries or any other fruit.
In greased muffin pan, fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon date nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks, flour, extract and soda. Mix 3 or 4 minutes on medium speed. Add dates and pecans. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 250° for 2 hours and 45 minutes to 3 hours in a stem pan lined with brown paper. White raisins may be substituted for dates.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside.
Pour cake mix into bowl and add oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add jello mixture and lemon.
Pour into greased and floured 9X13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.
While cake is still hot, prick all over cake with fork.
Make glaze with lemon juice and powdered sugar; pour over cooled cake.
Can also use orange cake mix and orange jello.

title: richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate and salt.
Add water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while it is still hot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Put cooked spaghetti and vegetables in a bowl; set aside.
Combine vinegar, oil, seasoning, salt, garlic powder, and cheese.
Mix well. Pour over spaghetti and vegetables. Marinate 24 hours.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Mix Italian dressing and Worcestershire sauce.
Place meat in Ziploc bag and vegetables in separate Ziploc bag.
Divide marinade between them.
Marinate meat and vegetables for several hours.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour into container and refrigerate.

title: magic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Place on bottom of baking dish (rectangular).
Spread graham cracker crumbs until it soaks into the butter and it looks dry.
Spread chocolate morsels. Spread butterscotch morsels.
Spread coconut.
Cover entire ingredients with condensed milk.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in casserole dish.
Season to taste. Pour tomatoes over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini drops
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, soda and oil.
Beat in eggs, flour, cinnamon, salt, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Add milk and stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add chicken, ham, rice (or macaroni), celery, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into greased 1-1/2 qt. casserole dish. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 5 more minutes until cheese melts.

title: beef vegetable stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 1 hour (or cook in slow cooker on low for 3 to 4 hours).
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs.
Combine flour, salt and soda; blend.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat well. Add variation.*

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix and chill ingredients. Serve with raw carrots, celery, peppers, onions, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: chow chow
directions: Let this come to a rolling boil, then pack in glass jars and seal.
(Leave out hot pepper, if you wish.)

title: vegetable medley stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the orange juice and cornstarch until well blended. Add the honey, soy sauce, vinegar, and red pepper sauce, stirring to combine. In a large wok or 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat the olive oil and sesame oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking. Add the carrots, sweet red pepper, and onion and stir-fry for 8 minutes. Stir in the orange juice mixture and cook for 1 minute or until the sauce boils and thickens. Stir in the sesame seeds if desired. Serve with grilled poultry or beef and brown rice.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 3 minutes or until water is almost gone; cool.
Add together with remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: nana's apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and cinnamon.
Add flour.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve in squares, with or without whipped cream.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Make meat into 6 patties and place in pan.
Slice vegetables and place over the meat patties.
Season with salt, pepper and margarine.
Seal mixture with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat the oven 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add in the eggs and mix thoroughly.
Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring.
Add into the creamed mixture.
Mix the salt and vanilla with the buttermilk in a small bowl.
Alternately add this and the flour into the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Mix the baking soda and vinegar together.
Gently fold into the batter mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to cool completely before frosting (recipe to follow).

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour with soda.
Add oatmeal, chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix milk and vinegar; let set while you cut flour, shortening and salt together.
Add milk and make dough.

title: yeast rolls and butterscotch rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, softened in water.
Add egg; gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.

title: tomato soup
directions: Brown bacon with butter, carrots and onion.
Add chopped tomatoes, sugar and 2 cups warm water.
Add 2 bouillon cubes.
Boil and add 1/4 cup rice.
Turn to low and simmer until thick.
Stir now and then.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon flakes.
Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into 4 or 5 big patties or make several small ones.
Pan fry in small amount of vegetable oil until browned on both sides.
Serve on hamburger buns.
If you make large patties, substitute egg white for whole egg for low cholesterol.

title: carol's carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except onions.
Heat gently until cheese is melted.
Put in serving dish.
Top with green onions.
Serves 6.

title: swedish toast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into 2 greased and floured pans (4 1/2 x 13-inches).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Slice and place on a cookie sheet.
Place in oven again for 13 to 15 minutes or until desired color of toast.

title: spanish meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into balls and place in a casserole dish.
Blend soup and water.
Pour over meatballs. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: aunt ritchie's zucchini
directions: Trim off both ends of zucchini.
Parbroil until tender, but not mushy.
Drain and cool.
Cut in halves lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Stuff the zucchini with bread mixture, dividing it evenly.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° until golden.
Serves 8.

title: banana muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Fill muffin liners 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix above ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and Raisin Bran.
Then add the eggs, buttermilk and margarine.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps up to 6 weeks.

title: pineapple-glazed apple pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups of the pineapple juice and the sugar.
Bring to boiling.
Add apple wedges.
Simmer, covered, 3 to 4 minutes or until apples are tender but not soft. With slotted spoon, lift apples from pineapple liquid; set apples aside to drain.
Blend the remaining 1/4 cup pineapple juice slowly into cornstarch; add to hot pineapple liquid in saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook 1 minute more. Remove from heat.
Stir in the butter or margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cover and cool 30 minutes without stirring.
Pour half the pineapple mixture into the baked pie shell, spreading to cover bottom.
Arrange cooked apples atop.
Spoon remaining mixture over apples.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Before serving, garnish center of pie with whipped cream and chopped Macadamia nuts, if desired.

title: taco bake
directions: Add water to above ingredients & simmer 25 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil or bake chicken until tender.
Boil broccoli according to direction on package until tender.
Layer chicken and broccoli in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Mix lemon juice, margarine and soups together.
Pour the mixture over the chicken and broccoli. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove and sprinkle cheese over the top. Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup, water and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook on Full power for 20 to 22 minutes until hard ball stage is reached.
Stir once or twice during cooking.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at high speed with mixer until mixture is thickened and candy starts to lose its gloss.
The beating may require 12 to 15 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts to beaten mixture.
Add food coloring if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add jello.
Cool slightly.
Add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top each slice with whipped cream.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.
Place marshmallows on top; return to oven for 10 minutes.
Cool cake 1 hour before icing.

title: sausage - cheese balls
directions: Crumble sausage into large bowl.
Add cheese and mix well. Blend biscuit mix into sausage-cheese mixture.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: poke cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine, 1 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to butter, sugar mixture. Stir in blueberries. Spoon into lined muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar. Makes 12 large or 18 regular muffins.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove bones and cut into shreds. Chop fine cabbage, onions and pecans.
Mix all together, adding salt and pepper to taste and a little celery, if liked.
Mix with two forks as lightly as possible (not mashy), then add in same way this dressing:
Rub the egg yolks fine and mix with the mustard, sugar, raw egg and cayenne pepper.
Add slowly the butter, juice of a lemon and vinegar, beating at least 1/2 hour, the longer the better.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve with crackers.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cracker crumbs, brown sugar, cinnamon and oleo; set aside.
Beat cake mix, water, oil and eggs in large bowl at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes scraping bowl often.
Pour about 2 1/3 cups batter in floured pan.
Sprinkle about 2 cups crumb mixture.
Pour remaining batter into pan and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 45 to 50 minutes; cool.
Drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: ratatouille
directions: In a 12-inch electric skillet, heat oil to 300°.
Saute onion and garlic until tender but not brown, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn heat control down until light goes out (simmer point).
Simmer approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender but not overcooked.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: monkey breakfast bread
directions: Grease with butter or margarine a large Bundt pan.
Place whole package of dough balls evenly as possible in pan.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over dough balls.
Melt margarine and stir in sugar and nuts.
Pour mixture over dough and pudding.
Cover with a tea towel and let raise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "nanna's scrumptious chicken"
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bag.
Put chicken pieces in, a few at a time and shake until coated.
Fry in hot oil in frying pan, browning all sides.
Mix together honey, mint and spices.
Brush onto chicken.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Turn pieces over and brush honey mixture on again.
Cover and cook 15 minutes more. Great with rice!

title: meat loaf sauce
directions: Stir tomato soup and brown sugar to get lumps broken up.
Put into a small saucepan.
