Bring to a full boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
It will thicken and darken.
Serve at once over meat loaf.
This is very good.
My family really enjoys it. The sauce will work on any of your favorite meat loaf or meatball recipe.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, salt, baking soda and powder together in one bowl. In another bowl, cream shortening and sugar together. Then add egg and milk; mix well. Incorporate the dry ingredients. Mix in bananas and nuts. Grease one standard loaf pan and pour in batter. Bake 1 hour.

title: friendship or 30 day cake
directions: Stir all together everyday. Use a wooden spoon.

title: best broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender.
Just use enough water to cover broccoli so you won't have to drain.
Add soups and milk to broccoli.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat down and simmer.

title: b. g.'s sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain, then crumble.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: beef stew
directions: In large skillet, put the first 4 ingredients.
Brown together, then add the next 4 ingredients.
Put this in tomato juice before putting in skillet, then add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Lots of vegetables can be added or substituted for those listed. Examples are canned green beans, mixed vegetables, potatoes, mushrooms, etc., but I would go with either all fresh or all canned, not a mixture, except for the sliced onions.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Cook on low heat until it thickens.
Layer cookies and sliced bananas in a bowl.
Pour thickened hot pudding over cookies and bananas.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Cook noodles, rinse and drain.
Brown meat, add onions and green pepper.
Cook until soft.
Stir in paste or sauce.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and cream cheese (blend with beater). Combine olives and almonds.
Place a layer of meat mixture in pan. Spread a layer of cheese mixture, top with olives and almonds. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
Pour milk into eggs.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix and pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll and cut to desired thickness. Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: abbie's coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix flour with sugar. Add coconut, canned milk, water, sugar and egg yolks. Cook until thick. Add oleo and vanilla. Pour into baked crust. Beat egg whites until thick peak forms; add 1 teaspoon cream of tartar and 4 or 5 tablespoons sugar. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and mix well. Put meringue on pies and sprinkle coconut on top. Brown in oven at 375°.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Lightly grease baking sheet.)
Decorate with sprinkles.
Children's favorite.

title: walnut broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut and brown tofu lightly in 2 tablespoons oil.
In pan, boil carrots and broccoli for 1 minute.
Drain and reserve liquid.
In wok, saute onions in 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat until soft. Then add mushrooms and walnuts.
Increase heat to medium high and add carrots and broccoli; stir.
Add tofu cubes; stir again.
To the reserved water add cornstarch, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour over the vegetables and tofu, then stir and cook everything until bubbling.
Serve hot over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, then drain.
Mix other ingredients into squash mixture until of custard consistency.
Put in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle buttered Ritz crackers on top of casserole.
Freeze or bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and onions through food chopper.
Add all other ingredients to a boil.
Boil 2 hours or until thick.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
As soon as sauce is of desired consistency, pour into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 2 hours. Stir and drop on wax paper (bite-size).

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt;
stir.
Beat in molasses, shortening and yeast mixture with 1 cup rye flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add
remaining
flour mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn
onto
lightly
floured board.
Knead until smooth and no longer sticky.
Bake in oven at 350° (makes 2 loaves). Bake until dark brown (not burnt).

title: ham and cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then add the onion a little at a time until it is mixed well.
Spread a little of the mixture on a slice of ham until ham is covered well.
Then slowly roll the ham and then slice about 4 times; it looks like a circle.
Lay flat on serving tray and chill.
These go over very well for any party or shower.

title: stir-fry venison supper with gravy
directions: Melt butter in cast-iron frying pan.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir-fry on fast heat until desired doneness. Remove all ingredients.
Add mushroom soup to pan drippings and heat through to make gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Stir in 2 2/3 cups warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and 5 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Divide in half; roll each half into rectangle, 18 x 9 inches.
Roll up like a jelly roll and place in bread pan.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Brush with butter and cool.

title: sauerkraut with spareribs and dumplings
directions: Place spareribs in bottom of 3-quart pressure cooker with 1/2 cup water.
Place sauerkraut on top of ribs, sprinkle 2 to 3 teaspoons brown sugar on top of sauerkraut.
Cook approximately 30 minutes; reduce pressure.

title: tea mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Store in container.
Use 2 tablespoons of tea mix to 1 cup hot or cold water per serving.

title: diabetic banana pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of a glass pie plate with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas over the wafers.
Combine all other ingredients in top of double boiler and cook until thick.
Pour over bananas.
Sprinkle crumbled wafers on top.

title: western omelette
directions: Mix eggs with milk.
Heat oil in pan.
Pour in egg mixture. Reduce heat and cook until almost done.
Add ham, green pepper, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold in half and cook another 4 to 5 minutes.

title: plain risotto
directions: Heat olive oil and butter in a saucepan on medium high heat. Add onion and saut until soft.
Add rice and saut until rice is coated.
Add white wine or vermouth and stir until all the liquid is absorbed.
Add hot broth 1/2 cup at a time, until it is all absorbed in the rice and rice is tender.
Add hot water if more liquid is needed.
Stir in parmesan cheese and fresh parsley, and serve warm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix, drop and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: breakfast pockets
directions: Roll out 1 biscuit and add egg, meat and cheese.
Fold the biscuit around the filling and bake according to biscuit directions.
You can substitute any kind of filling to make pizza, taco, chicken, etc., pockets.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed and set aside.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Drain and chop mushrooms and brown in butter.
Combine and pour in a casserole dish.
Top with 6 slices of dry bread crumbs and 3/4 cup oleo or butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Add 1 or 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: huckleberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, milk and shortening together.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mix and mix thoroughly.
Fold in berries gently so as not to crush.
Pour into prepared (either greased or sprayed) loaf pan and bake at 350° to 375° until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix together in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in a glass pan or at 350° in a metal pan.

title: italian sauce
directions: Brown garlic, onion and sausages in oil.
Add tomatoes, 3 cans water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Boil for 30 minutes, then add tomato paste and 1/2 can water.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: horseradish green beans
directions: Cook beans, onion and meat for 1 hour.
Combine mayonnaise, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and parsley flakes. Season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic salt, celery salt and onion salt.
Let stand at room temperature and spoon over drained hot beans.
Leftover beans are good cold.

title: bread crumb cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and water until thick and yellow.
Add sugar; beat.
Add rest of mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Spread chopped nuts over sheet.
Stir eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients and spread over chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on floured (powdered sugar) towel.
Roll up towel and cake. Let cool.

title: country beef and cabbage
directions: Saute potatoes and onions in oil in a large skillet.
Add cabbage and beef.
Cover tightly and simmer until cabbage is tender.
Season and serve.
Great with hot cornbread.
Makes a complete one dish meal.

title: lemon-chip cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg, lemon peel, lemon juice and water.
Stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in square semi-sweet chocolate, grated (1/3 cup).

title: home canned tomato soup
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Mix with enough tomato juice to pour.
Heat remaining tomato juice and add flour and sugar mixture, melted oleo, celery and onions.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put into sterilized jars and process 3 hours.

title: maine oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat egg, sugar, milk, maple syrup and oil.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Stir in rolled oats.
Bake at 400° in upper third of oven for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes (if you want to, cut them into quarters), boil them until you can stick a fork into them.
Once you can stick a fork in them, pour out all water and mash them.
Add all the rest of the ingredients while you are mashing until you get a good consistency.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, onions and green pepper until meat is cooked.
Add kidney beans, corn mix and salsa; simmer for about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Prepare plates with chopped lettuce and chopped tomatoes. Line outside of plate with tortilla chips.
Add meat mixture to center; top with sour cream.
I usually mix into sour cream some salsa to taste before topping meat mix.
It gives more flavor. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Enjoy.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: favorite dinner rolls
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: tavern soup
directions: Combine vegetables in slow cooking pot.
Add broth, butter, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in unsalted water until eggplant is tender, about 7 minutes; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese; mix well.

title: barb's dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple; save liquid.
Spread pineapple in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan; add filling, spreading gently over fruit. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling; top with nuts.
Combine melted butter with reserved pineapple juice.
Drizzle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and top with whipped topping.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Place graham crackers on cookie sheet; do not break apart. In stew pot, mix margarine and sugar.
Bring to boil on low heat; boil 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Remove from heat and pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Cut in bars while hot.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage; remove crust from bread slices. Spread with butter and cube.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with sausage; top with cheese.
Mix together eggs, half and half, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over top; cover and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: one step spinach lasagna
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
In large bowl, mix cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, lay 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 noodles and 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, then sauce and Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Pour 1 cup water around the edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes.
(Also you can take off foil for the last 15 minutes to brown.)
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown first 2 ingredients and drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then add corn muffin mix.
Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a pan, bring to a boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
In mixing bowl, put in sugar, flour and salt.
Pour boiling mixture over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, soda and sour cream.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix and pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° until firm and brown (45 minutes).

title: orange pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour in 3 parts, alternately with milk.
Add flavor last. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Start in cold oven.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix
cake mix according to directions.	Bake at 350° in small muffin pans that have been greased and floured.

title: potato-polish sausage and cheese dish
directions: Boil potatoes (about 1 quart), cut in bite sizes.
Cook until tender, no salt added.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Add half to the creamed mixture with 1 tablespoon of the water.
Add remaining ingredients and rest of water.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or round pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can be served warm with ice cream.

title: chris' light fruit dessert
directions: *Bananas, green grapes, purple grapes, strawberries, blueberries, peaches, kiwi slices, etc.

title: meat casserole
directions: Saute hamburg and onion.
Cook carrots, celery and rice.
Add to hamburg and onion and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place in casserole; sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: appetizer shrimp kabobs
directions: Peel onions. Wash cucumbers. Combine salt and water. Slice onions (optional bell pepper) and cucumbers with peel into 1/4-inch slices. Soak for 1 hour in the salt and water solution. Ice can be added to ensure crispness. Boil together the remaining ingredients. Remove onions and cucumbers from water mixture. Drain and add to the vinegar mixture. Bring just to a boil, about 10 minutes or until tender (do not overcook). Pack slices and liquid into hot, thoroughly cleaned jars. Let stand a couple of days before eating.

title: frito-grit casserole
directions: Boil grits in boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, cheese, Tabasco, eggs, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with crushed Fritos.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and allow to cool.
Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, mandarin oranges, pineapple and jello. Mix thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: mandarin orange filling
directions: Drain mandarins, reserving syrup.
Place syrup in small saucepan.
Use 2 tablespoons of syrup to dissolve cornstarch.
Add dissolved cornstarch and sugar to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add mandarin segments and heat through.
Remove pan from heat and stir in Triple Sec. Stir sour cream into mixture.
Fill omelets with mixture before folding.
This makes approximately 1 3/4 cups of filling, enough for 3 dessert omelets.

title: roast loin of pork
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow baking pan.
Combine ingredients and rub over roast.
Roast 35 minutes per pound.

title: aunt rissie's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar, eggs, water, pumpkin and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients: flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and pumpkin spice.
Mix all together until smooth.
Pour into three loaf pans or 6 gift size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Mix in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 1 hour until heated.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: atlanta fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice and bring to a boil.
Mix with jello; refrigerate.

title: italian sausage spinach pie
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and onion until the sausage is done and onion is tender, drain.
Separate one egg and set aside the yolk.
In mixing bowl, beat remaining egg white and whole eggs.
Stir in sausage, onion, spinach, Mozzarella, Ricotta, garlic powder and pepper.
Line a 10-inch pie plate with bottom pastry.
Add filling.
Top with upper crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top of crust.
Combine water with remaining egg yolk.
Brush over top of crust.
Cook at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Let set 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Cook ground meat until it crumbles.
Layer meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of onions, potatoes, carrots and cheese in that order until it is used.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
End with cheese on top.
Cover and bake in 300° oven until vegetables are done.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash, add soup, sour cream, carrot, salt and pepper. Butter casserole, sprinkle layer of crumbs in bottom.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs and generous dots of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Beat the cream cheese.
Mix in sour cream, garlic, salt and pepper until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into ball; roll in nuts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together the peanut butter and oleo.
Let cool.
Add the vanilla. Add the powdered sugar.
Mix together.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: swiss chicken breast
directions: Place breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese and mushrooms on top.
Combine soups, then spread over the cheese and mushrooms.
Sprinkle the stuffing on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: Prepare beef broth according to package directions.
In large skillet, melt butter and add meat, mushrooms, onion and garlic powder.
Cook until meat is browned.
Add beef broth, wine and lemon juice; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add salt and pepper, stir in sour cream and heat. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in round baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly, usually 1/2 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Break up cornbread or corn muffins and mix with mustard until consistency of potato salad.
Then fold in the remaining ingredients, except dressing.
Mix well.
Then stir in dressing a little at time until desired consistency is reached.
Serve.

title: grandma's freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onion.
Salt to taste.
Let sit 24 hours.
Rinse and drain.
Pack into jars or plastic containers. Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let cool and place in freezer.
Thaw before serving.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, together well.
Shape into a firm ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Cover or wrap and refrigerate.
The green ripe olives are what gives it a unique flavor.

title: gets raves chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with enough water to cover (with a little sage added) until done.
Bone and chop chicken into bite size pieces. Combine chicken, sour cream and soup (undiluted) in a large bowl; thoroughly mix.
Pack into a casserole dish, which has been sprayed with cooking oil spray.
Crush crackers, then spread the crumbs over chicken mixture.
Dot all over with small pieces of the stick of butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, cook butter until melted. Add garlic; cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes, or until butter is bubbly.
Mix in Parmesan cheese, parsley, lemon juice and shrimp. Cook on High for 2 minutes, or until shrimp are cooked.
Partially cover dish with Saran Wrap while cooking.
Serve over rice. Serves 2.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.

title: asparagus dip
directions: Drain asparagus; puree in blender until smooth.
Add softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic or onion salt to taste.
Blend until creamy.
Serve with crackers. Makes 3 cups.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Use liquid from oranges and add enough water to make 3 cups. Cook both boxes of puddings, jello and 3 cups of liquid.
Cook and stir until thick; cool.
Mix Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Pour in serving container and chill.

title: gingered ham and barley
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, orange juice and barley. Grate orange to make 1 teaspoon of zest.
Add to the barley mixture with salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and barley is tender.
Peel orange.
Discard peel and chop the orange.
Saute orange and onions in butter until tender.
Add to the barley mixture.
Spoon 1/4 cup of filling onto each ham slice.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon remaining barley mixture around rolls.
Mix marmalade and ginger.
Spoon over the rolls.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through. Yields 5 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs.
Mix flour and dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture.

title: fiery chicken
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Saute chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken and add onion; saute.
Put chicken back in pan, add flour and paprika.
Stir to combine.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes, turning chicken from time to time.
Add sour cream and peppers.
Blend.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes more.
Remove onto serving dish, top with chives.
Serve with rice or egg noodles. Serves 4.

title: kathy's cherry cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Pour melted margarine over the cake mix.
Spread nuts over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: seasoning mixture
directions: For variety, add 1/2 teaspoon of your choice oregano, marjoram, basil or thyme.
Put into salt shaker.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, marshmallows and apples.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
In morning, add nuts and celery.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, vinegar and sugar; blend well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Chill overnight.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, using whole can of mandarin oranges for the liquid.
Bake in 3 layer cake pans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chopped olives, salt and pepper to taste, chili powder and garlic powder.
Simmer.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer of sauce, layer of corn tortillas and cheese. Repeat layer for layer until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: garbage dip
directions: Finely chop all ingredients and mix well.
Best to chill overnight in order for the flavors to blend.
Dip with Doritos. After the first batch, you will probably need to make a double or triple recipe.
Serves 12.
Yields about 1 quart.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together. Add limeade, lime juice and food coloring. Pour into crusts. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Then add raisins, coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab and artichoke bisque
directions: Saute green onions, garlic and artichoke hearts in white wine and melted butter.
Then add seasonings.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients except the crabmeat and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Thicken with 1/4 cup cornstarch dissolved in a little chicken stock and gradually add to soup until desired texture is achieved.
Add the lump crabmeat and gently stir for 5 minutes.
Garnish with a thin lemon slice and a bit of paprika.

title: frosted chews
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in medium size saucepan. Stir to combine. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, mix well. Add Special K cereal, stir until evenly coated. Press mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 9 by 13 by 2 inch baking pan. Cool.

title: swedish toast
directions: Cream together	butter	and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Sift
together dry ingredients and add alternately with sour
cream
to
creamed
mixture;	mix well.
Add ground almonds; then spread
into
a
x	13-inch
pan (greased and floured) and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yummy wings
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the preserves, soup mix and dressing.
Stir well.
Place chicken wings in a large baking dish. Pour apricot mixture over the wings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cajun pretzels
directions: Mix oil and all seasonings with a fork.
Pour over broken pretzels.
Toss to coat.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours until dry. Stir often to coat.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: sour cream dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend soup mix with sour cream; chill.
Makes approximately 2 cups.
For a creamier dip, add more sour cream.

title: fettuccine italiano
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions, drain.
Toss with butter, garlic salt and cheese; sprinkle with black pepper.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Pie crust:
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Add butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: double-cheese chicken breasts in tomato sauce
directions: Fry breasts on electric skillet 10 minutes on a side at about 260°.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan.
Sprinkle half over one side of chicken.
Turn chicken and sprinkle second half on the other side.
Fry another 10 minutes on each side. Add onions to brown.

title: granola
directions: Heat 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Heat first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Heat together in stove.
Toast under broiler just to toast slightly.
Stir while toasting.

title: shrimp with pizzaiola sauce(scampi di pizzaiola)
directions: Make sauce and
add
peeled and deveined shrimp last 10 minutes of cooking
time.
Serve
with crusty Italian bread or over spaghetti, if desired.

title: jo's spring salad
directions: Mix dressing, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce. Grill chicken until done. Toss with remaining ingredients. Makes 4 servings.

title: tortoni
directions: Mix well the butter, crumbs, almonds and extract.
Set aside 1/4 cup.
Sprinkle 1/2 on bottom of an 8-inch pan.
Put layer of ice cream and 1/2 of the preserves.
Repeat.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs on top.
Put in freezer.

title: buttermilk delight
directions: Mix jello with pineapple and bring to a boil.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk and whipped topping until well blended.
Pour in molds or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate.
(I grease my dish with mayonnaise.)

title: tarika's pizza burgers
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Fill buns with meat mixture and serve with tossed salad.

title: hominy-cheese casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour; cook over slow heat.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Add onion, salt, chili powder and pepper; mix well.
Wash hominy and drain; stir into sauce.
Pour mixture into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly between additions.
Add flour, stirring by hand, not by mixer.
Fold in cream.
Distribute well, but do not overbeat.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch (25-cm) tube pan at 325° (163°C) for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spinach-artichoke-hearts of palm dip
directions: In a large frying pan or skillet, saut shallots and garlic in butter over medium heat. Add well-drained spinach, artichokes and hearts of palm and cook on low heat briefly.
Add cream, garlic/herb cheese, salt and pepper.
Simmer until cheese is melted and mixture is blended. Remove from heat and fold in Parmesan cheese. Serve warm with crackers or broken bread. Serves 12.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together by hand until smooth.
Add 8 ounces chocolate chips and stir.
Cook over low heat until done.

title: chickpeas indian style
directions: Open cans of chickpeas and drain, reserving liquid.
In blender or food processor place onions, ginger, chilies and garlic.
Blend this all together into a puree.
In heavy saucepan, heat 2 to 3 tablespoons oil briefly.
Add cumin, nigella and mustard seed.
The seed should pop and crackle.
(Do not let burn.)
Pour in blender contents.
Fry, stirring, until color turns golden.
Add coriander, tomatoes, salt, lemon juice and red pepper (if desired).
Mix well and gently mix drained chickpeas into the spice-onion mixture. Then add liquid from cans.
Cover and let simmer about 40 minutes. Tastes better the next day.
A good dish for vegetarians, too.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend everything but crab meat and half of cheese with mixer. Then stir crab meat into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola barbecue chicken
directions: Lay pieces in baking dish.
Slice onions on chicken.
Mix Coca-Cola and ketchup in bowl, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except beef, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Stir to dissolve tomato paste and flour.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes until vegetables are tender, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Microwave on High 1 minute until heated through.
Serves 2. Contains 269 calories, 8 gm fat and 532 mg sodium.

title: razor clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and save liquor. Chop clams into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces. Fry bacon until almost done and then add onion and celery; cook until tender. Do not drain, but set aside. Cook the potatoes separate and drain. Make a white sauce from the butter, flour and milk, adding the garlic, white pepper and salt to taste. Feeds 8 to 10 people.

title: san antonio casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion in oil.
In a large mixing bowl, combine soup and milk.
Stir until well blended; stir in chilies.
Fourth the tortillas and layer bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread with half of the meat mixture and half of the soup mixture.
Top with half of the cheese and repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Mix well with peppers and onion.
Place in a salad bowl.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in salad bowl.
Cover.
Let set 3 to 4 hours.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Spray casserole with Pam; put mixture in casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: stuffed-pepper casserole
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove ribs and seeds. Chop edible portion of tops; set aside. Wash peppers. Place peppers in large kettle with 2 quarts salted water. Bring to boiling; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Drain peppers; set aside.

title: tirami su
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon sugar until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon Espresso and brandy until smooth.
Add cheese and beat for 5 minutes.
Fold in the whipped egg whites until thoroughly combined.

title: honey and ham tortilla rolls
directions: With electric mixer, beat ham and cream cheese together.
Stir in pineapple, green onion and honey.
Spread 1/4 cup ham mix on each tortilla to within 1/4 inch of edges.
Roll up each tortilla, starting from one end.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours.
To serve, cut each tortilla roll into 1/2 inch slices and arrange on platter.
Makes appetizer servings for 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt cream drops and butter in microwave on Medium to Low heat for 2 minutes or until melted (do not overheat). Mix in peanut butter and stir thoroughly. Pour into a pie plate or casserole dish and chill until firm, then serve.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Add spices to cider.
Thaw orange juice concentrate over low heat; add brown sugar to taste.
Add juice to clear cider mixture and simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Add orange slices and cherries just before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute meat about 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomato, and simmer until tender.
Add tomato 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable stew(meatless)
directions: Leave onions and potatoes whole. Cut leeks, zucchini and celery into 1-inch pieces. Cut carrots in half.
Peel and quarter tomatoes.
Cut cauliflower into flowerets.

title: punch(weddings and parties)
directions: Mix well and chill.
You can freeze for later use.

title: chicken pie
directions: Prepare pie crust sticks according to directions and use half to line an 8-inch square casserole.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into lined dish.
Top with remaining dough and bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.
Serves 6 people.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, peanut butter and butter. Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cold water.
Boil until thick; remove from heat.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Put fresh strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour mixture over strawberries and chill. Add whipped cream.
Can be made with fresh blackberries, using blackberry Jell-O or use any fresh fruit, using the same flavor of Jell-O.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line bottom with wax paper. Sprinkle pecans over wax paper, then sprinkle coconut
over pecans.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Spread over cake mix.
Be careful not to spread on the edge.
Spread in middle only.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes. Cool and turn out to serve.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potato, flavoring and food coloring of choice.
Add as much as it takes to form the dough.
Roll out candy about 1/4-inch thick and spread a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll candy into a jelly roll and slice into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: double chocolate snack cake
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: mashed potatoes with cheese casserole
directions: Mash potatoes with canned milk.
Add Krazy salt or seasoning salt.
Add a pinch of garlic salt.
Make thinner than regular mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese and bake 1/2 hour in a 375° oven.

title: "joyous" chicken
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise into a sauce; pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add crumbs and cheese to top and bake last 15 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in strips.
Saute in olive oil and butter until browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Put zucchini and stewed tomatoes in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Mix eggs and Parmesan cheese to thick consistency (but spreadable).
Spread over top of zucchini/tomatoes.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly browned and hot.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Crush 1/2 of the wafers and line greased buttered pan, 12 x 8-inches.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well.
Spread this mixture over crumbs.
Whip heavy cream and add 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar.
Fold in 1 cup drained pineapple.
Spread over butter mixture and top with remaining wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate 6 to 12 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together and press into pie pan.
Bake about 10 minutes until light brown.	Set aside to cool.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine butter, brown sugar, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the first 2 items together.
Mix remaining together well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Slightly flatten each spoonful with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from pan before cool.

title: southern fried quail
directions: Season birds and roll in flour, coating generously.
Place in heavy iron frying pan, fat, shortening or cooking oil, 1/2-inch deep.
Cook until brown, cover, turn heat low and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove lid and turn heat up to crisp birds for about 5 minutes, turning often.
Make gravy with drippings, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, add rest of ingredients except 1 can soup. Pour it over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is gone.
Mix applesauce, sweetener, eggs and oil together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Gather into a ball shape and flatten.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix.
Add enough milk so it drops nicely.
Fry by tablespoonfuls in hot deep fat until golden brown.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: No Garden is Complete Without Turnips:

title: sweet pickles
directions: Dissolve
lime	in water, pour in sliced cucumbers, let stand 24 hours.
Wash
in clean water.
Let cucumbers stand in water for 3 hours.
Change
water every hour.
Rinse and drain well, make a syrup
with
sugar, vinegar and spices;
bring to boil and cool. Put
cucumbers in
syrup, let stand overnight. Next day, heat and come
to
a
bubbling
point.
Don't boil. Seal in hot jars.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, milk and sugar together.
Break angel food cake into small chunks and mix well with Cool Whip mixture.
Spoon into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix drained strawberries and glaze.
Spoon over top of cake/Cool Whip mixture. Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix the Cool Whip and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: miniature christmas fruitcakes
directions: In a saucepan, combine molasses, water and vanilla; add raisins and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; cool.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in fruit mixture; mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into paper-lined miniature muffin tins, filling almost to the top.
Bake at 325° for 22 to 24 minutes until cakes test done.
Cool on wire racks. Store in airtight containers.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: turkey log
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Roll into logs and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: linda's finger sandwiches
directions: Generously "butter spread" the mayo on each thin slice.
Put in chili strips and complete sandwich.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma dougherty's molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Cream shortening with sugars. Add molasses, eggs, water with soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and vanilla; mix well.
Slowly add flour.
Leave in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately, then mix all ingredients together.
Top casserole with cracker crumbs and melted butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, or 10 to 15 minutes in microwave on High.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift flour and salt together; blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
(Cookies do not spread.)
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool; roll in sugar again.

title: preacher's salad favorite
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until jello is dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meats until brown and crumbly.
Drain off grease.
Add velveeta cheese, oregano and worcestershire sauce.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake until brown at 350. These freeze well and can be baked frozen.

title: hostess twinkie cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with Twinkies|; cut in half.
Make pudding; pour over Twinkies| while hot.
Let set 2 to 3 hours. Pour pie filling over pudding; top with Cool Whip|.
Garnish with nuts or chocolate chips.

title: potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Cut potatoes and onion in slices.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, put one layer of potatoes and add 1 layer of onions, salt and pepper.
Then put another layer of potatoes and onions, salt and pepper.
Put one can cream of chicken soup on top and smooth out.
Pour 1/4 cup of water on top.
Cover and put in microwave for 25 minutes on High.

title: mexican cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate corn twisters and cut in half. Roll pieces into balls.
Press into baking cups, forming cup. Using 1/2 teaspoon, fill each cup with the following: chiles, salsa and cheese, Bake for 12 to 15 minutes on cookie sheet. Makes 36 cups.

title: light nuoc mam dipping sauce(nuoc mam lac)
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan over high heat. Bring to a boil, then remove from the heat.
Stir in the fish sauce.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Stir in the peppers. Serve at room temperature.
Makes about 2 cups.
(Keep sauce in the refrigerator for up to
1 week).

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Press mixed pretzels (or vanilla wafers), oleo and sugar in 9 x 12-inch dish and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crumbs when cooled.
Mix Jell-O and when it starts to thicken, put strawberries (thawed) into Jell-O and pour over top of mixture in dish.

title: mushroom cap salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in small saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add the mushroom crowns and simmer 5 to 6 minutes. Chill in a dish for several hours, stirring occasionally. Drain.
Makes 2 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown sausage.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle on grated Cheddar.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugar, salt and pepper; add corn and milk.
Place in a greased casserole dish (or spray with nonstick spray).
Dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable and 5 way rice casserole
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a large bowl and stir well. Pour salad dressing over the rice and vegetable mixture and toss gently. Cover and chill. Toss again before serving.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Use heavy soup pot.
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium heat until very soft (about 20 minutes).
In blender or food mill, puree soup in batches.
Return soup to cooker and reheat before serving.
Garnish as desired.

title: cheese grits
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until set.

title: wild rice mushroom soup
directions: Bring 1 can chicken broth to a boil in a small saucepan. Remove from heat.
Add mushrooms.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain well, reserving liquid.

title: luncheon showboats
directions: Combine; place on lower half of buns.
Heat in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Place top bun on just enough to heat.
Can be placed under broiler, but watch carefully.
Serves 8.

title: frozen chocolate mousse(serves 4)
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Pour into blender or mixing bowl. Add powdered sugar and blend.
Add eggs (1 at a time) and flavorings.
Whip the cream and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into muffin pans or parfait dishes.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds or chocolate shavings.
Freeze until set.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Melt butter and
mix
with
the
oatmeal mixture.
Pour 1/2 of this into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and press to form a crust.
Cover the crust with the applesauce.
Add the remaining oat mixture to the top of the applesauce.
Use a spoon to smooth and press lightly into a top crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together; stir into shortening mixture.
Mix in pecans, cherries and dates.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and store in tight container.
Cookies keep well for several weeks in a cool area. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: whiskey cake(jim beam)
directions: Mix at medium speed the cake mix, pudding, eggs, 1 1/2 sticks oleo and 1/2 cup whiskey for 2 minutes.
Stir in butterscotch chips and walnuts.
Bake in tube pan.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and poke holes in cake with toothpick.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar; add milk and vanilla slowly. Add one cup of shredded coconut.
Pour in crust.
Bake at hot (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to slow (325°) and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cappuccino
directions: Combine all ingredients. Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of mix and 6 ounces hot water.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Beat in blender. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat in saucepan big
enough
to
hold largest piece of chicken.
Put chicken on grill.
For
last 10 minutes or so of cooking, dip each piece in
sauce
and
return to grill.
When finished with last piece, go back to first, dip and replace on grill on other side.
Dip
one
more before placing on serving platter.
Reserve remaining sauce for serving.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Heat chicken stock.
Combine all ingredients and add to stock and mix well. Put into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and add Jell-O.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or rectangular pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan in order.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef.
Boil noodles to desired softness.
In a casserole dish, combine beef, noodles and tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: rumaki
directions: Wash and halve livers.
Drain well.
Put livers in buttermilk. Place 2 to 2 1/2 cups of flour in bag.
Place livers in bag.
Shake well.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Wrap each liver in a piece of bacon. (Cut bacon in half or thirds; make it long enough to go around livers.)
Place wrapped liver on a broiler pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake livers 25 to 30 minutes at 400° or until bacon is crisp.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Shape into a ball and coat with pecans.
Yield:
1 cheese ball.

title: "frank's indian chili - hot"
directions: Cook first three ingredients on top of stove in a cast-iron skillet and cover until meat is done; stir often to insure mixture.
Add all peppers to meat as it is cooking.
When all ingredients are finished cooking, transfer them to an 8-quart cast-iron pot.
Add 1 gallon pork and beans; stir until ingredients are mixed.
Add 1 tablespoon dry crushed red pepper seeds and stir until mixed.
When mixture is hot, add cheese. Stir in cheese; let cook on a low/medium setting for approximately 45 minutes.
Turn off stove.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Reheat next day and serve.

title: curried potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into 1-inch chunks.
Steam until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and put in large bowl.
Add raisins, scallions and almonds.

title: jiffy lemon pie
directions: Set out pie shell.
Blend thoroughly the condensed milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and egg yolks.
Pour into shell and set aside.

title: pecan drops(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Start oven at 325° and chop pecans rather coarsely.
Cream butter and shortening together until smooth, then beat in confectioners sugar gradually.
Stir in flour thoroughly and add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until a very delicate light brown.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil 1 cup sugar, marshmallows and 1 cup milk.
When melted, add coconut and spread on warm cake.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: baked beans quintet
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Cook onion and garlic in drippings, stirring constantly, until tender; drain.
Combine bacon, onion mixture, butter beans and next four ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in catsup and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in refrigerator. Stir well.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugars, butter and eggs.
Add flour, pumpkin, water, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into four greased and floured 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yields 4 mini loaves.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all dry ingredients. Cut in shortening and mix with hands.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture and mix.
Keep covered in refrigerator until ready to cut out biscuits.
Remaining dough can be kept in refrigerator a week or two.
Bake biscuits 12 minutes at 400°.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, milk, eggs and oranges on medium speed 3 minutes. Spread in 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured. Bake 25 minutes. Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, cracker crumbs and milk in 1-quart casserole. Mix well.
Stir in egg. Dot with butter.
Cover.
Microwave 8 minutes on Medium or until set.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes, covered.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Cook and drain spinach.
Add all ingredients to egg mixture and stir. Melt butter in 10-inch square pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake 30 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes after baking.
Serves 6.
May be made a day ahead.
May substitute broccoli.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Drain oysters. Cut bacon slices in half and fry until partially cooked.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around each oyster and secure with a toothpick.
Broil, about 4 inches from source of heat, until edges of oysters begin to curl and bacon is cooked. Makes 22 to 24 angels.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths, cut onion into eighths.
Coarsely chop onions.
Add along with garlic to butter in 3-quart saucepan. Add onion and saute 1 minute.
Add potatoes and pour in broth. Simmer 20 minutes.
Puree soup in food processor or blender.
Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.

title: italian zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon.
Pour into greased baking dish (8 or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
May be served as appetizer by serving smaller portion.

title: corine's cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour in pan (best in iron skillet).
Bake until brown in 450° oven.
Don't forget to use oil in the skillet before pouring in mixture.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes.
Beat margarine until creamy, then gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats to mixture and mix well.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, then pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch strips; salt, pepper and flour.
Brown meat in the butter; add chopped onion and mushrooms.
Add the 1 bouillon cube to 1 cup hot water; add to meat mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes; during this time cook rice or noodles.
Stir in the (1) cup of sour cream into the meat mixture; do not add when meat is too hot or cream may separate.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Enjoy!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish but marshmallows.
Sprinkle them on top; cover and bake 1 hour or until bubbles.
Let cool and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet milk doughnuts
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; blend carefully.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add alternately with combined milk, shortening and vanilla to first mixture.
Chill dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and roll.
Cut with floured cutter.
Fry in 365° deep oil until brown, turning once, if necessary.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional).

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well corn meal and flour; add boiling water a little at a time.
Use a little warm water to make the batter just right.
Let set overnight or longer until sours a little.
Buttermilk will make it sour faster.
Once you are ready to bake, add salt, sugar, soda and baking powder.
Grease pan and bake until brown.

title: sharp cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Mix flour, red pepper, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg, milk and butter separately and stir into dry ingredients only until just moistened.
Lightly stir and fold in 1 cup of the cheese.
Spoon into muffin cups and top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes until golden brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: berries with raspberry sauce
directions: Hull and halve strawberries.
Sort through blueberries and fresh raspberries.
Place berries in a large serving bowl and press through strainer to remove seeds.
Stir in sugar and lime juice to taste.
Drizzle sauce over fresh berries and let stand at room temperature until ready to serve.
Spoon berries into dessert dishes.
Top each serving with small scoop of ice milk or fat-free frozen yogurt.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: country stew
directions: Mix ingredients together in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours, covered with foil.
No peeking while cooking.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden.
Serve warm.

title: best turnips
directions: Peel turnips with a vegetable peeler and cut in chunks. Cut apple in chunks. (Apple may be peeled according to your preference.) Place in pot with margarine, and sugar; add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes, or until the turnip chunks are tender. Serve hot.

title: potato rusks
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together.
Beat eggs, then add salt and shortening.
Mix with first mixture.
Then add flour and knead like bread.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and keep punched down until you want to bake.
Then pinch off small pieces and work in a ball.
Place on greased pan close together.
Let raise. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Combine cheese and crackers.
Mix butter, soup and reserved asparagus liquid together.
Add ham, if desired.
Layer in casserole dish in this order:
cheese and cracker mixture, asparagus spears, almonds and half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cracker mixture on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This can bake longer.
(Good for suppers that wait.)

title: peppies (pecan fingers)
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into fingers.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Remove from oven and roll into powdered sugar while still hot.
Cool on waxed paper. Roll in sugar again before storing in layers of waxed paper.
Good at Christmastime.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a
greased casserole dish. Brown ground beef and onions; add rice. Place rice/meat mixture over cabbage. Pour soup and water over the top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cassava pineapple cake
directions: Squeeze and discard liquid from grated cassava. Cream sugar and butter. Add slightly beaten eggs and salt. Mix well. Stir in coconut milk, grated cassava and crushed pineapple. Pour into greased square pan (8 x 8). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 55 minutes or until light brown in color. Pour pure coconut cream on top. Bake for another 5 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 12 to 15.

title: turkey breast italian
directions: Put turkey breast in crock-pot. Heat rest of ingredients until bubbly. Pour over turkey and let cook all night on low or 6 to 8 hours on high. Shred turkey breast and put back into crock-pot. Cool broth until fat rises to top, remove fat and pour back over turkey. Serve hot on hoagie buns or Italian bread.

title: b.l.t. salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix with sour cream, mayo and milk in a large bowl.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, bacon and cheese; stir.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, toss to coat well with the dressing.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Combine asparagus, onion and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once. Cool mixture slightly.
Process asparagus mixture in blender or food processor until smooth.
Set aside.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of a large baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Mix the soup and water together until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle onion soup over top. Cover with foil and place in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 250° and bake about 2 hours.
I leave it in the oven while we are gone to church on Sunday.
It's very good and easy!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly first six ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: date nut cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder over nuts and fruit; mix well, then add sugar.
Add egg yolks, beaten well.
Stir vanilla into the yolks.
Lastly, beat egg whites and mix well.
Grease pans and line bottoms with paper.
Fill to top (does not rise much).
Bake slowly for 2 hours at about 275°.

title: hamburger and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook carrots 10 minutes.
Place in casserole.
Cover with potatoes.
Pour soup over top.
Place remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well with hands.
Spread mixture over soup and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Add cornstarch to cold water and mix.
Add boiling water and stir until thick and clear.
(May have to thicken on stove.)
Let cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add the sugar and beat until stiff.
Add cornstarch mixture and mix well until stiff.
Beat in the vanilla.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake for 10 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: canned dill beans
directions: Lay green beans flat in a big pot; cover with water and cook 30 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Pack green beans in pint jars, standing beans on end.
Place 1 garlic bud in each jar.
Cover beans with boiling liquid mixture.
Seal.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite size; boil 5 minutes and drain.
Cook bacon in skillet.
Chop onion into grease and simmer.
Sift flour over grease and brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cabbage.
Place in dish and top with grated cheese. Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: first grade sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the butter generously over all sides of the loaf.
Place the bread on baking sheet in the oven. Remove the loaf from the oven when it is evenly browned, about 15 minutes.

Slice the loaf lengthwise and hollow out the interior, leaving as much bread along the walls of the loaf as desired. Fill the insides of the loaf with peanut butter and jelly to taste. Arrange the banana slices inside the cavity or, if desired, layer the slices between the peanut butter and jelly. Close the loaf.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sinful salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine jello and boiling water.
Stir with rubber spatula until jello is completely dissolved.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Shape into small balls and bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Preparation time: 5 minutes. Yield: 50 balls.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread, milk, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl, mixing well.
Add ground beef, onion, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup catsup; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place on lightly greased rack in a broiler pan. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Combine remaining brown sugar and catsup and spoon over loaf.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Let stand
5 minutes before serving.

title: yum yum cheese cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Chill until set. Top with filling and refrigerate.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix and store in large, airtight container.
Use 5 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine first four ingredients and shape into balls, a little smaller than a walnut.
Place balls in refrigerator and chill. Melt chocolate chips, along with 1/3 bar of paraffin wax.
Dip chilled balls.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the ingredients well and roll into bite size balls.
Dip in chocolate glaze.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Measure 1 cup dry cake mix.
Set aside. Stir together remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil in a large bowl (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture lightly into bottom and three quarters of the way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potatoes with chorizo
directions: Put oil in a pan.
Add potatoes; let them cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until they are cooked, then add onion and chorizo for a few minutes.

title: delicate meltaways
directions: Beat softened butter, cornstarch and vanilla to blend.
Add flour and sugar; beat until creamy.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Freeze clams overnight.
When frozen it is easy to open them with a dull kitchen knife.
Chop clams while frozen and put in a bowl.

title: friday seashell salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Add next 4 ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve on well chilled lettuce leaves.

title: fruit-filled muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch or line with paper baking cups.
Stir milk, oil and egg in medium bowl until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients except fruit preserves and stir until moistened. Divide batter evenly among cups.
Drop 1 level teaspoon fruit preserves onto center of batter in each cup.
Bake 13 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from pan. Drizzle with glaze.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Mix 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake oblong 40 to 50 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Cool.
Frost with Sour Cream Chocolate Frosting.

title: all season grilled chicken
directions: Mix chili sauce, vinegar, horseradish, garlic and salt in a bowl.
Reserve half of mixture.
Add chicken to bowl; turn to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade; place chicken on grill or on broiler pan. Grill or broil; turning and basting frequently with the reserved marinade; about 30 minutes.
Serve remaining marinade with chicken.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and rice in large cake pan.
Place chicken on top, salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour uncovered.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: potatoes parisienne
directions: Peel the potatoes and with a melon ball cutter, form as many potato balls as possible with each potato, placing them in cold water to prevent discoloration.
Place potato balls in boiling water (lightly salted) and boil for 4 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter in saute pan and when medium-hot, add potato balls. Saute until lightly golden.
Serve immediately.
May be prepared up to time of sauteing.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: kris' easy muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Add oatmeal.
Stir well.
Add sugar and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Fold in berries, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook on medium heat until mixture forms a ball (about 5 minutes).
Cool and knead.
Store in airtight plastic container when not in use.

title: cauliflower and carrot casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots, salted to taste, separately, in small amount of water.
Drain and arrange half of cauliflower in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add drained layer of carrots and half of cheese.
Repeat with remaining cauliflower, carrots and cheese.
Top with undiluted soup and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until very hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and sift.
Add pecans and stir to coat.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to flour mixture.
Pour into 3 (1 pound) coffee cans that have been well-greased and floured.
Fill cans half full.
Bake 2 hours or until tested done in a 250° oven.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all and bake 1 hour in 3 or 4-quart casserole dish at 300°.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Cook noodles.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, hamburger, noodles, sauce and cheeses; repeat, making sure last layer is cheese.
Heat in oven for 20 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: hawaiian pineapple "poke" cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool entirely, then poke holes in cake with rounded spoon.
Drain completely pineapple.
Spread pineapple over baked cake and press lightly, for pineapple to go in holes.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a large skillet.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients except cheese in a large bowl and add ground beef mixture.
Stir lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover lightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: special k cookies
directions: Boil sugar and syrup 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir until peanut butter is melted.
Pour mixture over cereal in a large mixing bowl.
Coat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into two greased 9-inch aluminum foil pie tins. Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 35 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat broiler.
Line shrimp on broiling pan.
In 1-quart saucepan, add crushed garlic, marjoram and spices.
Pour over shrimp and broil for 5 to 8 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Put on a serving platter and arrange lemon on ends.
Serve with pasta or rice.
Serves 6.

title: sandies
directions: Cream the butter, flour and powdered sugar together. Add vanilla. Form into balls the size of large pecans with a nutmeat inside.
Bake in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
When light brown, remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: macadamia nut dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk with mixer until smooth.
Stir in sour cream, horseradish, onion, green pepper, pepper and garlic salt.
Spoon into ungreased, shallow, 2-cup baking dish and set aside.
In skillet, saute nuts in butter.
Sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and milk in saucepan until melted. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over sauce and lay rolls on top.
Let raise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn over onto foil.

title: stained-glass hard candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over medium heat until the mixture reaches 300° (hard crack stage).
Remove from the heat; add food color and flavoring. Pour mixture onto an oiled cookie sheet.
When thoroughly cooled, break into pieces.
Yield: about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix 7/8 cup sugar with flour and sift three times.
Beat egg whites in electric mixer until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar and continue to beat until egg whites are just stiff enough to hold their shape.
Add remaining sugar to eggs 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at medium speed.
Add vanilla and almond extracts and continue beating for two minutes.
Then gradually fold in sugar and flour mixture with rubber spatula and continue folding for another two minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mince peppers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at about 300° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: crisp potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Cool, then cut into quarters lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Reserve pulp for other recipes.
Increase oven temperature to 500°.
Combine butter and soy sauce; brush on both sides of skins.
Bake on baking sheet 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp.
Top with your favorite topping.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the green beans and put in a medium bowl.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup.
Put mixture in a baking dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer the pan with pecans and coconut.
Cream butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese in a bowl and set aside.
Mix up cake mix as directed on the box and pour on top of pecans and coconut.
Pour butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese mixture on top of cake mix.
Cook in oven for 1 hour.
Take out and let stand for 4 hours, then turn over and dig in!
(Or, you can leave it in the pan.)

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and vanilla extract.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into a greased baking pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add cheese, pour in crock pot (sprayed with PAM or oil).
Add margarine.
Beat eggs and mix with both milks; add to macaroni mixture.
Mix and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: grated cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and grate.
Mix next five ingredients and add to grated potatoes. Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower cheese casserole
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Arrange in a shallow 2-quart well buttered baking dish.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan.
Add red and green pepper and garlic.
Saute for 1 1/2 minutes.
Sprinkle over cauliflower.
Mix cornstarch into milk.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to frying pan.
Stir in milk and cornstarch mixture; cook, stirring until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese is blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or cover and refrigerate. Bake for 35 minutes, if chilled.

title: chilled cranberry soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine cranberries, water, sugar, cinnamon stick and cloves.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until about half of the cranberries are popped.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and orange peel.
Cool.
Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Before serving, remove cinnamon stick.

title: nana's date loaf
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and milk; boil to soft ball stage. Add dates; cook until melted.
Add nuts and vanilla; cool.
Beat until thick, roll in wet cloth.
Cool completely, slice and store in refrigerator.

title: mom's jello salad
directions: Combine the lime Jell-O and crushed pineapple and bring to a boil. Then let cool. Add remaining ingredients to the cooled Jell-O and pineapple mixture. Chill.

title: long john silvers fish batter
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Dip fish; deep fry.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over hot water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix. Spread candy in buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: easy fettucini
directions: Heat soup, milk and cheese.
Toss noodles with butter. Combine.
Serve with extra Parmesan cheese.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown the bacon; break into small pieces.
Remove bacon from pan.
Brown the celery and onion in the bacon drippings.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine the beans, bacon, celery, onion, molasses, catsup, mustard, salt and bean liquid.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover when the beans and sauce seem to have thickened enough.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Saute the first two ingredients in butter or margarine.
Add shrimp to onion and carrot; saute about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milks.
Add salt, pepper, Season-All salt, garlic salt and cheese. Heat until cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Thicken with cornstarch/water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onions, crumbs, egg, ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Mold into a round flat loaf and bake in a 9-inch pan at 350°.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken, onion,
celery
and
salt
in water until chicken is tender.	Remove	chicken
from broth and cool.
Cut meat into small chunks.
Add soups	to 1 1/2 cups of broth and stir.
Arrange tortillas in pieces	in
bottom of buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole.	Cover
with chicken chunks.
Sprinkle with green peppers and Ro-Tel
chilies.	Pour
soup
mix
over all. Sprinkle with chili mix.
Cover
and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40
minutes.
Remove
from
oven
and
