sprinkle cheese on top.
Return
to	oven
and
cook,
uncovered, until cheese is bubbly.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Put in boiling salted water.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Put in bottom of 9 3/4 x 9 3/4 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Stew together tomatoes, peppers and onion.
When all vegetables are cooked (nice and soggy), pour over eggplant. Sprinkle on oregano, black pepper, salt and top with grated Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges in a large bowl. Blend on low speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 38 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Spread each tortilla with mixture.
Roll up and slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: meat potato bake
directions: Put meat and onion in pan.
Brown.
Add salt and stir.
Melt butter or margarine in another pan.
Add flour to melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add milk a little at a time.
Stir as you add milk.
Cook until thick to make sauce.
Stir as it cooks.
Put half of potatoes in a baking dish.
Add half of meat, then add half of sauce.
Add rest of potatoes, meat and sauce.
Cover baking dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and brown under broiler until brown, about 5 minutes.
This recipe doubles well.

title: petite french cheesecake
directions: Mix first four ingredients until creamy and fluffy.
Place 1 wafer in bottom of cupcake liner in cupcake tin.
Fill each cup 2/3 full with mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, garnish with filling.

title: potato squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a microwave safe bowl, combine the potatoes, squash and water.
Cover and cook on high for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place half of the mixture in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble sausage over potato mixture.
Top with onion and remaining potato mixture.
In a small bowl, combine flour and 1/4 cup cream until smooth; stir in remaining cream.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine uncooked rice, ground meat, salt, pepper and a small amount of tomato soup.
Mix and form into 12 meat balls.
Place in a greased 3-quart covered casserole (or electric skillet for browning).
Heat margarine in skillet and lightly brown green pepper and onion.
Blend in the flour and add remaining tomato soup slowly.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake.
Serve from casserole or on heated platter.
Serves 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oven to 500° and place the bread pan in the oven to heat. Beat the egg slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Grease the pan.
Drop the mixture from a big spoon and cook 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pinch off desired amount and roll into balls; let rise one hour.
Cook at 350° in a greased pan until brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Store remaining dough in refrigerator.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Set oven for moderate (350°).
Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg, then applesauce.
Mix and sift the flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir in alternately with water.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured oblong cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cool on rack.
Frost as desired.

title: tasty green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and cook for 1 hour or more.
These taste like fresh beans and are low-fat.

title: broccoli roll-ups
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Snip corner of pouch and drain butter sauce into a small saucepan.
On floured surface, roll each biscuit into a 5-inch circle.
Divide broccoli into 10 spears.
Arrange 2 spears on center of each biscuit and top with ham.
Fold biscuits sides over broccoli and ham and pinch to seal.
Place biscuits, seam side up, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Prepare cheese sauce.
Stir flour and mustard into butter sauce until thickened and smooth.
Stir in cheese and mushrooms and cook, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Serve roll-ups with sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and shape into balls. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham balls.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add oil, molasses, salt and milk.
Gradually stir in 3 cups flour and beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour.
Knead about 10 minutes or until dough springs back to touch.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Divide into thirds and shape into loaves.
Place in well-greased pans.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes until golden.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water. Add strawberries and stir until separated. Add pecans, bananas and pineapple; mix well. Put half of mixture in chilled dish. Pour sour cream for middle layer and remainder of strawberry mixture on top. Chill for several hours.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown chopped onions and pepper in butter.
Add to beef and cook.
Drain grease.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add all to soups and peas (sprinkle cheese on top).
Bake in large flat dish for 3/4 to 1 hour slow.

title: cold curried apple soup
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add apple, carrot, green pepper and celery and saute until vegetables are soft, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in cloves, curry, parsley and nutmeg.
Add broth and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in whipping cream.
Transfer to blender in batches and puree.
Pour into bowl. Cover and refrigerate.
Garnish each serving with cream and apple.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into Ziploc bags (can easily be doubled).

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour with yeast.
Heat and stir milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm.
Add to flour mixture along with the eggs.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 1 to 3 minutes.
Using a spoon, stir in as much of remaining flour as you can.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes total).
Shape dough into a ball.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour (for high altitude, punch down and let rise again).
Punch down and turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Grease muffin pan and put 3 little balls in each one (approximately 1 tablespoon per ball).
Cover and let rise in warm place, about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 12 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 rolls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° until tender, cool and remove skin. Mash or whip potatoes in a large bowl. Add butter, sugar, salt, spices, vanilla extract. Set aside. In a small bowl, beat egg yolks slightly.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cut and wash mushrooms; set aside.
Mash both meats in pan over high heat; pour off enough drippings in another pan to lightly brown rice.
Then add to meat the onions, pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until onions are clear; add tomatoes, chili powder, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Add rice to meat mixture.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt margarine. Saute onion; add and saute green chilies. Add and melt cream cheese; add cans chunk white chicken. Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons mixture into tortilla shells. Roll and place seam side down into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch dish. Top with Monterey Jack cheese and drizzle with small container whipping cream. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in balls and in white sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with sour milk and mashed bananas to shortening mixture until smooth.
Add nuts and bake in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean from center of loaf.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Cut up chicken breasts if desired.
Place chicken breasts in casserole dish and pour mixture over chicken and mix together if you choose to cut chicken up. Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Garnish tray with lettuce or other greens.
Place pineapple spears on tray and heap cranberry mixture on pineapple.

title: cashew brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and butter in a saucepan. Stir over medium heat to 300° on candy thermometer.
Add cashews. Cook until thermometer reaches 310°.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Smooth out to fill the pan.
Let stand until cold, then break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crush the entire package of Oreo cookies.
Crush until the creamy middle disappears.
(This makes the "dirt" for the cake.)
Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add the sugar and the Cool Whip, mixing well.
Combine the milk, vanilla pudding mix and vanilla extract.
When set, add this to margarine and cream cheese mixture.
Put 1/2 of the "dirt" on the bottom of the oblong pan.
Put prepared filling mixture on the top of this.
Add the remaining "dirt" on top.
Chill several hours before eating.
(You can put in a toy sand bucket or flowerpot if you like.
You can also put the jelly worms on top.)

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Pour butter over bread cubes to coat.
Mix tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and basil.
Pour over bread.
Mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured cloth-covered board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Transfer rounds to piece of waxed paper that is heavily covered with granulated sugar; turn each round so that both sides are coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick round with fork 4 times.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Put cookies together in pairs with creamy filling.

title: alice's fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar. Add eggs.
Mix in pear honey.
Sift dry ingredients and mix 1/2 cup fruit and nut mixture. Add to creamed mixture, then add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Makes 3 medium size loaves.
Bake in preheated oven at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin praline pie
directions: Combine pecans, soft butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Spread on bottom of pie shell.
Prick sides of pie shell and bake 10 minutes in hot oven.
Cool 2 minutes before filling with pumpkin mix.

title: fast fudge
directions: Add first five ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stir while cooking until it comes to a boil (approximately five minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels to marshmallow mixture, stir until the chocolate melts. Add the pecans and vanilla.
Spread evenly into a 8 or 9 inch buttered square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 dozen squares.

title: dried apple cake(very old)
directions: Mix apples while hot with soda.
Add margarine and sugar, well creamed; add all the spices and flour.
Then add raisins and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° in 2 deep 9-inch pans or tube pan. Frost with favorite brown sugar frosting.

title: honey-whole wheat bread
directions: Mix wheat flour, honey, shortening, salt and yeast together with mixer; add warm water.
Mix 1 minute on low speed, then 1 minute on medium speed.
Stir in flour, 1 cup
at a time, until dough can be handled.
Knead dough 10 minutes on flour.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover 1 hour.
Punch down, divide in half, rise 5 minutes and flatten to form rectangle.
Place in greased pans. Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with oats.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: coconut or chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add milk and coconut.
Beat egg yolks and add to cooking, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
If making chocolate pie, then add 1 cup of chocolate instead of coconut.

title: cinnamon spread
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.
Use on hot breads, toast, or muffins.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour into an oblong glass pan (8 x 11-inches).
Mix jello, boiling water and ice cubes until jello begins to gel.
Mix in pineapple, cranberries, nuts and marshmallows in jello.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: barley soup
directions: Place lima beans in mixing bowl.
Cover and soak overnight. In large soup pot, place soup bone, celery, onion and enough water to completely cover bone.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until meat is very tender.
Remove bone from soup pot and cut off all edible meat from the bone; return meat to pot.
Discard bone and membranes.
Drain beans and add with remaining ingredients to pot.
Adjust water to make 4 quarts of soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 or 6 hours.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and butter; press into 9 x 9-inch pan. Arrange peaches to cover crumbs and sprinkle on the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake until bubbly.
Remove from oven and pour on already beaten milk, egg and syrup mixture.
Return to oven and bake until firm.
Oven heat is 350°.

title: busy day salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl, sprinkle jello, stir to mix an let set for 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Fold in oranges and pineapple and topping.
Spread into square serving dish that has been lightly oiled or sprayed with pam.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Can be made day before. Let sit overnight.

title: soy grits omelet
directions: Beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Add soaked soy grits and blend thoroughly.
Add salt and water to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold in yolk mixture and pour into skillet containing the hot oil.
Cover and cook slowly over a low flame until set around edges.
Remove cover.
Place in moderate oven for 15 minutes to complete cooking and allow to brown slightly on top.
Fold over and serve.
Serves 4.

title: after-dinner mint shake
directions: Place 1 cup of the ice cream in a shaker cup.
Add 1/4 cup milk, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and a few drops of mint flavoring. Apply seal and shake well.
Repeat and serve in 12-ounce glasses.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Defrost shrimp if frozen.
In large skillet, fry bacon and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add rice to vegetable mixture, blending well.
Cook until rice turns opaque and white.
Add broth, tomatoes, oregano and salt.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and cover.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add prepared shrimp and bacon to rice mixture.
Cover.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until shrimp is pink.
Fluff rice.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with lemon wedges.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together until smooth. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg. Mix vanilla and milk together and add to the mixture. Add baking powder to flour and sift, then add to mixture and beat on low for 2 minutes. Then beat on high until creamy and smooth. Pour into a well-greased and floured tube cake pan. Put in oven and then turn oven to 325°. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken parmigiana sandwiches
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, bring the tomato sauce, tomato paste, onion, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano and the red pepper flakes to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low; simmer for 2 minutes.
Preheat the broiler and line a broiler pan with foil. In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, bring the chicken broth and sherry to a boil.
Add the chicken, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon oregano and the black pepper.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until fork-tender.
Refrigerate until cool; peel and chop potatoes and 5 eggs.
Reserve 1 egg for garnish.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except reserved egg and paprika.
Quarter or slice reserved egg; garnish top of salad.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 7 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in small amount of shortening, then place in casserole dish. Add rice, water, salt and onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Do not lift foil until chops are done.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix together well.
Spray an 8-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can double this recipe to make long cake pan full.

title: grilled reuben sandwich
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, catsup, horseradish, parsley and pepper.
Spread this sauce on bread.
Layer the corned beef and sauerkraut on 4 slices of the bread and top with the cheese. Cover with the remaining bread and spread with 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Melt the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter in a large nonstick frying pan over medium heat.
Add sandwiches, unbuttered side down, and fry until golden, about 5 minutes on each side. Turn and brown the other side.
Makes 4 servings.
Work time:
25 minutes.
Total time:
25 minutes.

title: apple skillet cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet, measuring 10-inches across top. Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar.
Arrange apples in skillet. Add raisins.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Add brown sugar and sugar gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, water, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; stir.
Add chocolate bits.
Mix well.

title: fudge
directions: Combine ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, and cook in saucepan until it is in soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thickened and glossy.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Serve when cooled.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and crushed pineapple, then sprinkle jello over and mix.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add nuts.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients (except parsley and nuts).
Mix well and
chill	at
least
2 hours (better overnight).	Shape into ball and roll into nuts and then into parsley.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with cocktail bread slices or crackers.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix and serve with assorted fruit.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel apples and cut in half; remove core.
Wash and lay aside to drain.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well and spread on plate.
Refrigerate until firm.
Layer chopped lettuce, onion, olives, tomatoes and green pepper.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Leave set in refrigerator overnight. Serve with taco chips.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into two bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to boil.
Boil about 2 minutes more, until thick and clear.
Add the strawberry gelatin.
Stir until melted.
Cool slightly, but while still hot, pour over berries arranged in pie shell.
Be sure to cover all berries.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: easy streusel pumpkin pie
directions: Beat together butter, coffee powder, salt and almond extract. Gradually beat in sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Stir in flour and chocolate pieces.
Press batter into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Set pan on rack. Cut in 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars while warm. When cool, remove from pan.
Makes 40.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 5 or 10 minutes until it is thick.
Take off heat and cut 1 pound Velveeta cheese in this. Add beaten eggs and Tabasco; mix well.
Add little chili peppers to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 can evaporated milk to form a dough. Press 1/2 of dough into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt caramels and remainder of milk in a double boiler. Pour on top of cooked dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the chocolate chips and nuts.
Form remainder of dough into small flat circles. Place on top of chips and nuts.
Sprinkle remainder of nuts and chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add rice and stir until browned.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10-15 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: linguine with roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a small saucepan, combine stock and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Place in blender or food processor, along with vinegar, and puree until smooth.
Return to saucepan and keep warm.

title: french dressing with tomatoes
directions: In jar or airtight container, place all ingredients, except last two.
Shake well.

title: cauliflower spaghetti
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add crushed garlic, bay leaf and basil.
Saute one minute.
Add cauliflower and sprinkle with salt and saute until tender.
(Can add water and cover to steam cauliflower until tender.)
Add tomato puree and lower heat to a simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Toss with butter and oil and half the cheese mixture.
Put spaghetti on a platter and pour cauliflower sauce over the spaghetti.
Top with the other half of the cheese mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients, but corn.
Add to corn and pour into greased casserole.
Set in pan of water and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tight jar.
Use 1/3 cup of mix in large mug.
Add boiling water.
Stir.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Place candy bars on bottom of pie shell.
Blend all ingredients.
Pour over candy bars.
Then bake at 450° for 5 minutes and then 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool; serve with Cool Whip. Cut in tiny pieces because it is very rich.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except mayonnaise. Mix lightly with mayonnaise. chill thoroughly. Serve on salad greens. Garnish with grated cheese. 6 servings.

title: lime salad
directions: Add 2 tablespoons sugar to whipping cream. Mix all ingredients. Place in a Jell-O mold.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Mix together, then add 1 (12 ounce) Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze overnight.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy.

title: meatless spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings; simmer 1 hour.
Toss with 8 ounces (dry weight) spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: oven beer stew
directions: Put in roaster and cover.
Cook in oven for 8 hours at 250°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients, adding mayo last.
Toss together.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a large bowl to soft peaks. Beat at high speed in electric mixer. Add 1/2 cup of sugar, gradually sprinkling 2 tablespoons at a time, to the egg whites and continue to beat until very stiff peaks are formed. Do not underbeat.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Boil the eggs, sugar and butter over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly as it burns easily.
Cool, then pour over the remaining ingredients.
Mix and press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli rice ii
directions: In a saucepan, bring to a boil the water, margarine and onions. Add remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into a baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: potted apples
directions: Cut in slices.
Take out core and stem and cut off bad spots. If apples are sweet, use 8 cups.
If apples are tart, use 10 cups.
Cook until most of liquid is out about as you would with dried apples.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with garlic; roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with oil on both sides.
Add soup mix, mushrooms with liquid and water.
Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or toast.

title: punch
directions: Put ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour pop over ice cream.
Allow 45 minutes before serving, stirring often.
Easy to make and real good.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil, pour over flour mixture and stir. Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Cream margarine and gradually add sugar and blend in eggs.
Beat well at low speed and add dry ingredients alternating with pumpkin.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate bits.
Put mixture in well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, then bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Let stand 6 hours before slicing.

title: old fashioned hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir in sugar gradually (about 1/4 cup at a time). Mixture will be dry and thick.
Add salt, then slowly stir in evaporated milk.
Continue cooking for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and chicken; spread on bottom of baking pan.
Melt margarine.
Add broth.
Make stuffing and place on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Lightly sift together the remaining ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture until blended. Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour in 2 grease and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine cereal and milk. Let stand 10 minutes or until milk is absorbed. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; set aside. Add pumpkin, oil, eggs and raisins to cereal. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined 2 1/2-inch muffin cups; fill to top. Sprinkle each muffin with 1 teaspoon cinnamon sugar. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan and remove to eat! Makes 9 muffins.

title: cream of hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms and milk.
Season to taste.
Let simmer.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Wash and cube peppers, onions, cucumbers and carrots.
Place all veggies in a large bowl. Cover with water and 1 cup salt.
Let stand at least 3 hours or overnight.
Put vinegar, sugar and spices in a large enamel pot; bring to a boil.
Add the veggies; again bring to a boil.
Ladle the veggies into hot jars.
Add the hot liquid to cover veggies.
Put tops on immediately and seal by immersing in a canning kettle or large pot of boiling water. Leave quart jars in for 10- minutes, pint jars for 5 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Add fudge topping; mix together. Place in refrigerator.
Use one large teaspoon for cup.
Pour hot milk over it.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Mix together in heavy saucepan.
Heat slowly until sugar is dissolved, then bring to a boil.
Pour immediately over 3 stiffly beaten egg whites that have salt and vanilla added.
Beat until cool and spread on cake.
This frosting does not get hard and sugary.
Spread coconut on top and sides.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak pieces in hot grease.
Add soy sauce and water. Lay vegetables on top of meat and cook with lid on until almost soft.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Taste to see if more water is needed and if soy sauce is too salty.
Serve over rice.
Do not add salt or pepper to steak.

title: spicy cheese sandwich
directions: Wash and dry the greens and lettuce.
Leave some parsley for decorating the plate.
Chop the rest of the greens fine.
Butter the bread and place a lettuce leaf on top.
Mix the cheese, salt, pepper, greens and seeds.
Spread on top of the lettuce and put a sprig of parsley in the center.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press melted butter and vanilla wafer crumbs in a pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1 1/2 sticks soft butter and confectioners sugar until fluffy.
Add pineapple.
Slice bananas on top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: strawberry banana shake
directions: Place in blender and process until smooth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Line pan with coat paper first.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Combine with green pepper and onion.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler.
Take off stove and add milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in buttered pan and keep refrigerated.
Nuts may be added.

title: elegant amaretto-chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook until chocolate melts.
Dip larger end of each almond into chocolate and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Gradually stir Amaretto into remaining melted chocolate; set aside.
Combine gelatin and water in a medium saucepan.
Beat egg yolks slightly; stir into gelatin mixture.
Add sugar and milk, mixing well.
Cook over low heat, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate mixture.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
pour
over roast.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove foil; bake about an hour or until meat is tender.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in alternately with apple sugar mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Let stand in pan to cool.
This cake is good plain or with cream cheese frosting.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes in a 7 x 11-inch glass flat casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Marinate at least 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt oleo; add to crumbs until mixed well.
Use on bottom; save some to sprinkle on top.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add vanilla.
Mix in all the rest. Place on baking sheet in golf ball sized mounds.
Compress slightly.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Simmer grape jelly and chili sauce about 1/2 hour.
Mix hamburger, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown and drain.
Put browned meat balls into hot sauce and simmer 1/2 hour.
Very nice appetizers.

title: unfired fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly by running them through a food chopper or blender. If necessary, add a little fresh fruit juice to make a thick paste. Press into a loaf pan. Freeze in freezer. Slice before serving.

title: spicy beer-cheese dip
directions: In skillet, cook garlic in olive oil over medium-high heat 2 minutes or until browned.
In bowl, combine Cheddar spread, cream cheese, beer, mayonnaise, paprika and sauteed garlic.
Cover; chill overnight.
With a serrated knife, cut off top of bread loaf; set aside.
Hollow by running knife around inside of crust to release bread center.
Spoon cheese mixture into the bread bowl.
Cover with top for easy carrying along.
Cut center of loaf into cubes and serve with spread.
Makes 3 cups (16 servings).

title: chocolate kiss cookies(valentine treat)
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Stir butter and peanut butter together until well mixed.
Add sugar and egg; mix.
Take a small amount of dough and roll it between your palms into a ball about the size of a big marble.
Place balls on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Push a chocolate kiss into the center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen Chocolate Kiss Cookies.

title: old fashion southern lemonade
directions: Add ice cubes to water and set aside to chill.
Roll, wash, squeeze and dice into bits, the rind and pulp of lemons into mixing bowl.
Add juice, sugar and lemon bits; mix well.
Add about 4 cups of chilled water.
Add to the remainder of the chilled water.
Pour some of the lemonade mixture back into the mixing bowls to make sure the lemon mixture was all added to the chilled water.
Repeat if necessary.
Refrigerate until time to serve with ice cubes. Yields one gallon.
Original.

title: oven baked chops
directions: Melt butter on stove.
Dip chops in melted butter.
Crush crackers.
Pour in pie pan.
Dip chops in crackers.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and salt and pepper a little.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: communion bread(heritage)
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Work into soft butter and milk.
Make into a ball.
Put into a Ziploc bag. Beat with mallet 200 strokes.
Take out and divide into 4 balls. Roll each ball between wax paper.
Roll very thin.
Cut in strips. Bake at 325°.
Do not let it brown.
While still warm, cut into bite size pieces.
Pack in airtight box.
Save 2 or 3 long strips for pastor to use in the service.
Recipe makes enough for Pisgah. Very old recipe, used at Pisgah for many years.

title: pink peppermint surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
For cake, add peppermint extract and 6 to 8 drops food coloring to egg white packet and water.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.
Serve each cake slice with vanilla ice cream, chocolate fudge ice cream topping and crushed peppermint candy.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on two 9-inch round tins or one 13 to 14-inch pizza pan for crust.
Bake and cool.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add the egg and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into small balls and dip the top in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add boiling water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat the sweetened berries with the gelatin until the gelatin dissolves.
(Do not add water.)
Set aside to cool.
Beat together the milk and pudding.
Stir in the sour cream, then fold in the frozen whipped topping.
Layer wafers, pudding mixture and strawberry mixture.
Repeat, topping with pudding mixture. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger with the onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Place meat into casserole dish.
Stir in drained green beans and tomato soup (do not add any water to soup).
Top with mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil together brown sugar, margarine, salt, vanilla and corn syrup for 5 minutes.
Mix well occasionally.
Remove from heat and add baking powder.
Stir in quickly.
Pour over popped corn mixing well.
Put in 2 large flat pans and place in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Add 1 package nuts.

title: cabbage crown
directions: Combine ground beef, flour, salt, pepper, egg and nutmeg. Blend thoroughly.
Add onion and milk and after mixing, set aside. Trim off outward leaves of cabbage.
Slice off 1 inch from core end with sharp knife and hollow out cabbage to leave a shell 1/2-inch thick.
Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Fit cut slice back into place and tie with kitchen string.
Place stuffed cabbage, core end down in Dutch oven.
Add boiling water and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: snacker crackers
directions: Mix dressing, oil, garlic powder and dill in a large bowl. Add crackers, mixing until well coated.
Let stand about 1 hour before serving.
Store in an airtight container.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add chopped onion and green pepper. Simmer 15 minutes and drain again.
Add tomato sauce and garlic salt. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: nacho fondue
directions: In a saucepan, stir soup.
Stir in cheese and milk.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth and bubbling, stirring constantly.
Stir in salsa.
Heat through. Serve in fondue or small crock-pot with chips or fresh vegetables for dipping.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cherry brisket(make two days ahead)
directions: Season meat with soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle on soup mix.
Add rosemary, caraway seed and celery seed. Marinate two days.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Boil slowly until onions are done.
Pour over ribs, chicken, etc.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes.
Fry bacon; drain and cut up. Put bacon and onions in a bowl.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and flour in water.
Add potatoes and serve.

title: green rice
directions: Chop celery and onion.
Saute celery and onion in oleo until limp, not brown.
Cook broccoli according to package directions. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes. Cool.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: mexican chicken stew
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients except onion to skillet; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook 10 minutes. Stir in cooked chicken and onion; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
If desired, serve with tortilla chips or corn bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate mousse cheesecake
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
In large bowl, beat first three ingredients thoroughly.
When mixture is smooth, beat in cocoa.
Fold in Cool Whip just until mixed.
Fill crust and chill for four hours.

title: three cheese baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine cottage cheese, eggs, and parmesan cheese; set aside.
In another bowl combine hot pasta and pasta sauce.
In 9x13 dish, spoon in half of pasta mixture, and evenly top with cheese mixture, then remaining pasta. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes. 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in pan.
Pour in batter and fruit.
Bake at 350° until done, 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper with a teaspoon.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Line pan with tortilla shells (can soften with chicken broth).
Then layer chicken, pepper, onion and a mixture of Ro-Tel, soups, chili powder and garlic salt.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry cool whip
directions: In large bowl, mix cherries, pineapple,
milk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover. Chill. Makes 5 cups.

title: granny-honey's flank steak
directions: Marinate steak for 1 to 2 days, turning often.
Pour marinade over steak.
Cover loosely with foil to keep from burning.
Broil 35 minutes.
Cut very, very thin slices against the grain.
Serves 8.

title: turkey or chicken salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder, onion and chutney. Assemble all other ingredients except nuts. Toss all this well with mayonnaise mixture. Place in refrigerator overnight so flavors will blend. Toss with nuts before serving.

title: chocolate fudge kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: red beans, rice and kielbasa
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, saute bacon until lightly brown. Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until soft.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour to mixture; roll out dough and cut.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: passover butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cake meal, nuts and orange peel and mix well.
Roll onto aluminum foil and shape into a roll about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all the water is gone.
Mix applesauce, sweetener, eggs and oil together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Add all ingredients and thicken to your liking.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake until thickened, about 20 minutes.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix with a mixer.
Pour into pie crust and chill at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pizza steak
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Set aside. Mix flour, oregano, basil, thyme, salt and pepper on small plate. Cut steak into 8 pieces.
Dredge with flour and spice mix.
Place in baking dish.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Beat everything together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 more minutes.

title: granola bars
directions: *To toast oats, place 2 cups dry oats on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken livers
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam.
Roll livers in flour.
Brown these in margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
When almost cooked, pour in dry onion soup mix, sherry and water.
Stir and let simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over fluffy, boiled rice.

title: sausalito delight
directions: Layer sliced tomatoes around a platter.
Place a sprig of basil on each and top with cheese.
Drizzle generously with oil and dash of vinegar.
Serve with any main course.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and add the eggs sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well, gradually add the sifted flour, baking powder and soda.
Place half mixture in a buttered 9-inch tube pan and sprinkle half of the topping mixture over.
Place remaining dough on top and sprinkle with the remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crab cheese ball
directions: Mash cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Gently blend in crab meat, Worcestershire sauce and Old Bay seasoning by hand.
Spread parsley flakes on wax paper.
Form cheese mixture into a ball and roll evenly in parsley flakes.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours (preferably overnight) before serving.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/2 cup milk.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts.
Put 3/4 of the mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramels on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Crumble rest of crumb mix over top.
Bake again for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: liver italienne
directions: Brown liver in oil.
Combine Ragu with water.
Add to liver along with onions.
Heat to boiling, then turn to low and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: sweet raisin bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, margarine, salt and cinnamon.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; combine with milk mixture.
Add eggs plus egg yolk; mix well.
Add some of the flour, then the raisins and the rest of the flour.
Knead bread dough on a floured surface until it is smooth and does not stick to your hands.
Add extra flour a little at a time, if needed.
Place dough in a greased pan and cover it with a towel.
Allow the dough to rise in a draft-free and warm place until double in bulk.
Remove dough from pan and divide it into loaves.
Place in well-greased loaf pans.
Cover and allow dough to rise again until double in bulk, or just until it rises above the sides of the loaf pan.
Take 1 beaten egg white and brush the top of the loaves.
Bake.

title: sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar, bring Crisco, oleo, water and cocoa to rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Put in 8-inch pan. Double for large pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: light lemon salad
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Let set.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: grandma lepla's oatmeal filled cookies
directions: Mix and roll out thin the first 7 ingredients.
Cook until thick sugar, dates, water and vanilla.
Spread on the rolled out cookies.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: snicker bar dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip, ice milk and peanut butter together.
Add pudding mix.
Fold in Grape-Nuts.
Freeze.
Remove a few minutes before serving.

title: souper spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in butter.
Add soups, water, garlic salt and salt.
Cook spaghetti in 3 quarts water 8 minutes; drain.
In 3-quart casserole, combine meat mixture, spaghetti and 1/2 of cheese.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (the more cheese the better).

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Bake any chocolate cake following directions on box.
Combine pudding, sugar and milk.
Beat at slow speed.
Add in Cool Whip, then put on cake.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: corn flake chicken
directions: Dip chicken in evaporated milk; roll in corn flake crumbs, seasoned with Accent, salt and pepper.
Place in shallow pan lined with Reynolds Wrap in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium sized bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon (dry ingredients).

title: chili(sam's)
directions: Brown hamburger meat with small amount of seasonings.
Add onion bits; cook until done.
Set aside.
Saute onions and bell peppers in oil; drain.
Add to hamburger meat.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, chili block and seasonings.
Stir.
Cook for about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture in small amounts. Mix together.
Add grated apples and mix well.
Add pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish about 40 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except last 3) thoroughly in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool, then chill.
Beat cream cheese until soft; add sugar, then gently fold Cool Whip into cheese mixture.
Gently fold cheese mixture into pumpkin mixture which has been chilled.
Pour into pie shells.
This is delicious even without the addition of cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat.
Let sit for a few minutes, then add meat.
Roll into meat balls.
Brown in skillet, turning often.
Remove from skillet and place in a large pot.

title: tea and party pick-up
directions: Soften butter and cream with cheese.
Add sifted flour, salt and pepper; knead.
Pinch off one heaping tablespoon and mold in palm of hand around a date-stuffed with pecan half.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: wine jelly(low calorie)
directions: Combine wine, soda and sugar in saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over liquid.
Stir and cook over low heat until dissolved.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in food coloring.
Pour into containers and cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
May be refrigerated up to 3 weeks. Makes 16 ounces.
Contains 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Sprinkle bottom with a mixture of the powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 tablespoons chopped pecans. Mix the cake mix with sugar, sour cream and oil. Beat in eggs (one at a time), vanilla and 1 cup pecans (chopped). Pour half of the batter in Bundt pan. Sprinkle this with a mixture of brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Add rest of batter. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Let cool a few minutes before turning out on plate. Needs no icing.

title: easy cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese with mixer until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust. Chill at least 3 hours. (Better if chilled overnight.) Top with pie filling.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cook chicken (whole pieces) until done.
Broil I prefer. Place chicken in one layer in 9 x 11 pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle cheeses over chicken and sauce.	Bake at 350° until cheese melts and heated through, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: headmaster's sunday supper apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg and oil.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture with vanilla.
Fold in apples. Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool, wrap and store overnight before serving.
Freezes well, too.

title: barszcz(beet soup)
directions: Boil beets on medium heat in 4 quarts of water for 1/2 hour. Then add the rest of the vegetables and boil for 1/2 hour more. Add 1 pint of tomato juice.
Bring to boil for about 2 minutes. Add butter; stir in well.
Lastly, add cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve hot.
I add 2 small or 1 large potato.
I also use vinegar, about 4 or 5 tablespoons to taste.
It will keep a couple of days in a cool place and seems to improve with standing.

title: date cake
directions: Add boiling water to dates, soda and butter; let cool.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pans in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: quick ham broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken tikka
directions: Mince garlic, onion and ginger together.
Mix yogurt and cream together, then add to minced onion mixture. Add remaining ingredients except the chicken.
Cut each piece of chicken deeply like a tic-tac-toe game.
Marinate with the mixture 7 to 8 hours or overnight.
Grill.
Serve with a
salad.

title: pull bread
directions: Mix and work into a stiff dough.
Let rise twice in bulk. Then work down.
Roll on floured board like you would biscuits. Cut with biscuit cutter and pull each biscuit real thin.
Then press (standing up) together in a loaf pan.
Let rise again until it is twice in bulk.
Bake in 325° oven.
Makes a real good loaf of bread.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: microwave frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole with only water that clings to it.
Cover and cook 14 to 16 minutes on High. Rotate dish 1/2 way through cooking time.
Let stand covered 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt in 2 cup glass measuring cup and heat 1 minute.
Stir to blend, then evenly coat cauliflower.
Top with grated cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: venison sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and make into patties. Braise in butter with Cabernet Sauvignon wine, both sides, and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until cooked to your preference.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Combine coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight. Prepare cake by box directions into 2 layers.
After cool, split layers to make four.
Reserve 1 cup coconut mixture.
Pour coconut mixture between layers.
Combine Cool Whip and 1 cup coconut mixture; frost outside of cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat the egg whites until foamy and stiff.
Add the chocolate and nuts.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°, then turn off when light comes on.
Leave in oven (turned off) at least 4 hours or overnight if you can!
They melt in your mouth.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and flour.
Pour into 5 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over the rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: edora gunch (meat dish)
directions: Teenage boys told their grandma that they liked this dish.
For speed in preparation, I often leave out the uncooked rice and serve on a bed of rice instead.

title: berries 'n biscuits shortcake
directions: Combine jelly and orange juice, heat until jelly melts.
Cool. Wash berries and slice.
Pour jelly mixture over sliced berries and refrigerate.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and orange peel in a mixing bowl; cut in butter until crumbly.
Add milk and mix to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a buttered baking sheet and shape into an 8 or 9 inch round.
Pat top to smooth.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with a mixture of sugar, cardamon and pecans.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool to room temperature.
To serve, split shortcake and spoon berries over bottom half.
Replace top and ladle over remaining berries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with cherries and nuts if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chile verde
directions: Cut steak into small cubes; brown in oil.
Add chopped onion and fresh tomato.
Blend chiles, whole tomatoes and cilantro (chopped in blender).
Add to meat.
Add seasonings.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on top of stove.
Add flour and water when almost done to thicken.
Add more water if texture is too gooey.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spring casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Make a sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Cook until thick and add cheese.
Pour sauce over vegetables and pour the bread crumbs over the vegetables.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate sauce(good on ice cream sundaes, cake, etc.)
directions: In saucepan, melt butter with chocolate, sugar, cream or evaporated milk, corn syrup and vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 3 1/3 cups.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients, ending with flour. Stir in flavoring, coconut, pecans and cherries.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold into cake mixture.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans, greased and lined with waxed paper at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and trim broccoli; cut into medium size pieces.
Blanch 4 to 5 minutes, just to remove rawness.
Run cold water over and set aside.

title: frosty tomato cups(doubles as a salad)
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix into remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Decrease temperature 25° if using glass dish.
Done when knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Beat together with sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine rest of dry ingredients.
Stir into butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes. While that's baking, melt caramels and milk in microwave.
After 15 minutes of baking, remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture on top of it.
Add chocolate chips and pecans and place back into oven for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mexican fudge
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Cheddar and Chihuahua cheeses.
In a small bowl, combine salsa verde and eggs until thoroughly blended. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place half the cheese.
Pour the salsa verde mixture over cheese; top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares and place on tortilla, corn or nacho chips.

title: pork 'n rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Pour uncooked rice in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water and pour over rice.
Stir in mushrooms.
Place browned pork chops over rice and sprinkle onion soup on top.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan on top of the melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: *Note:
If you use canned clams, add these with liquid during last 5 minutes of soup making.

title: layered sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put half of the slices of potatoes in a casserole dish.
Add half of the brown sugar.
Dot with half of the margarine. Add a layer of cranberry sauce.
Repeat layers. Pour orange juice over top.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar;
cover and chill overnight.	Add apples, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse in cold water.
Combine oil and vinegar. Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour oil and vinegar over all. Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: mexican food
directions: Brown chuck; add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes. Spoon over Tostitos or corn chips.
Top with grated cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, peppers and onions.

title: coffee walnut cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda.
Folding lightly add coffee and chopped walnuts.
Mix well.

title: peanut chocolate dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir peanuts into flour mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust and chill.
Combine puddings and milk, beating 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate bar and chopped peanuts. Refrigerate.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix 2 minutes until peaches are cut up into small pieces. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: *If you don't like beans, substitute cooked Spanish rice (1 package).

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Roll pieces of cut up chicken in melted butter and then in mixture of Rice Krispies, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Place, skin side down, on cookie sheet.
Do not touch pieces together. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Do not turn.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix together ingredients.
For drinks, 1/3 cup of chocolate mix with 12 ounces hot water.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Mix well over medium heat.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet; add bread crumbs and stir.
When cool, sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook veggies as directed; drain.
Mix all ingredients together (except for crackers and margarine).
Spread in Pyrex dish.
Top with crushed crackers (Ritz or Club).
Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Spread cracker crumbs in 6 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs and mix up and press down evenly in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on crumbs, then butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Spread milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares when cool.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix by stirring together the soups and rice.
Place on baking dish.
Arrange chicken breast on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
No stirring, no turning.
Do not cover.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box except use the bananas and water for the amount of liquid. Add mace, salt, vanilla and margarine. Cook in a sheet cake pan.
If you use yellow cake mix instead of lemon, add a tablespoon of lemon juice.

title: heavenly seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions in 2-quart bowl. Spread dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl. Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with crisply cooked bacon slices, crumbled, and additional Cheddar cheese.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole dish.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat the first four ingredients to boiling (making sure all sugar is dissolved).
Cool completely.
Add next three ingredients.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Cut chicken in nuggets. Put enough oil in pot to cover chicken. Put chicken in bowl of flour, then in beaten eggs, then in flour with sesame seed. Drop in oil until it floats to top.
tags: bowl of flour with sesame seed

title: chili cheese burgers
directions: Combine sour cream, chili powder and 1 teaspoon salt; set aside. Mix beef, chilies, cheese, 2 teaspoons salt, cumin and pepper. Shape into 8 patties. Grill on gas grill, set at medium. Cook to desired degree of doneness (about 8 minutes each side). Top each patty with 2 tablespoons sour cream mixture and serve open face on half of bun. Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and pie filling.
Add oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce lined plates if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl and mix until smooth. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes a large cake.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and bell pepper.
While browning meat, add garlic powder and chili powder.
Stir and add salt and pepper to taste.
When meat is brown, add tomato sauce.
Rinse cans (about 1/2 can of water each) and add to mixture.
Add oregano and thyme.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles according to box directions.
When done, pour out 1/2 of water and add cool water to allow handling.
Layer noodles, cheeses and meat mixture. Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan.
Layer again.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: kaylen's chocolate crinkles
directions: In a medium bowl, mix cocoa, white sugar, and oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Stir into cocoa mixture.
Cover dough and chill for 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 350.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls. Roll and coat each ball with confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute and then cool on a wire rack.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Cover with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain in morning and add the other ingredients. Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking on bottom.
Add chopped celery and cook 10 minutes.
Put up in sterilized pint or quart jars and seal.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: brenda's spaghetti salad
directions: Toss everything in a large bowl and serve.
This makes a large bowl full.

title: punch
directions: Soften sherbet.
Add ginger ale slowly and serve.

title: taco pie
directions: In pie plate, spread softened cream cheese over the bottom. Pour can of chili on top of cream cheese.
Drain and paper towel dry green chilies and layer on top of chili.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk until well blended.
Add cherries and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done.
Start in cold oven.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend on low speed in mixer the cake mix, flour and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add oil and sour cream and mix until creamy. Pour 1/2 of batter into 10-inch tube or Bundt pan which has been greased and dusted with powdered sugar.
Mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over batter in pan.
Cut through with knife.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: crock-pot smothered chicken
directions: Prepare chicken like for frying (salt, pepper and flour). Place in crock-pot.
Pour in soup and water.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine with balance of ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover casserole with aluminum foil and bake 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: hearty dinner casserole
directions: Crumble raw turkey or beef in bottom of microwaveproof 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle frozen vegetables on top of meat. Sprinkle with minced onion and bouillon.
Thinly sliced potatoes; place in an even layer on top of vegetables.
Spoon tomato soup over potatoes.
Cover and microwave on High for 14 minutes.
Turn dish and microwave on Medium (50%) for 14 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend peanut butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and milk; beat until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: tahitian spareribs
directions: Cut
ribs
into
serving size pieces.
Place on rack in roasting pan and bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel, de-seed and finely chop cucumber.
Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet & sour wings
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper with any desired seasonings. Dip chicken in eggs and then into flour mixture. Coat well. Melt Crisco in large frying pan. Cook chicken on each side for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an 8 or 9-inch square pan combine cranberry sauce, apples and cinnamon.
In a bowl combine oats, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Add oil and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over the cranberry mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch.
Parboil in salted water.
Brown hamburger.
Add chopped onions, peppers, flour, salt, pepper, oregano and tomato sauce.
Layer in casserole alternately the sauce and eggplant with sauce last.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take from oven. While still hot, poke full of holes with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Cool; top with Cool Whip. Shave Heath bars, and sprinkle over cake.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: rancho beans
directions: Simmer onions in oil until golden. Add beef. Stir with a fork while onions brown lightly. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and freeze.

title: peas-n-mushrooms
directions: Partially thaw peas if necessary to get them free.
In small casserole dish, greased, place peas and all other ingredients, except stock.
Pour stock over mixture in bowl.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until peas are tender and mushrooms done.

title: carolyn's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and heat in microwave or on stove until melted.

title: salmon croque monsieur
directions: Drain and flake salmon; mix with mayonnaise.
Trim crusts from bread.
On each of 4 slices of bread, place a slice of cheese (trim to fit), 1/4 salmon mix and another slice of cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs with milk.
Coat each sandwich in egg mixture and saute on both sides until browned.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: grandma forsythe's peanut butter eggs
directions: You will also need plastic egg molds.

title: a-maizing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In bowl, mix corn, sugar and brown sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Add oil and beat until well mixed. Stir in raisins and nuts. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to liquid all at one time and stir until blended. Pour into greased 9 x 15 pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes (until cakes tests done).

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, heat until sugar dissolves, pineapple and sugar.
Spoon this over warm cake.
Prepare pudding according to directions and spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage stuffed shells
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prick sausage with fork and cook in a small amount of water in a covered skillet for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Chop sausage and fry along with onion until brown and crumbly, stirring often.
Spoon off fat.
Add egg, bread and parsley; mix thoroughly. Fill hot shells with sausage mixture.
Pour 1/2 the sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange shells in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes. Remove foil.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake, uncovered, 10 more minutes.

title: molasses jam cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Cream together butter, shortening and sugar and add molasses and jam.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks
into butter mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add with milk.
Beat egg
whites
until forms firm peaks and fold into batter.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make up cake as directed on box.
Bake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break cake in small pieces.
Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip, pineapple, cocktail, cherries, coconut, strawberries and nuts, then start again and again end with Cool Whip and coconut.
Make up and serve right away or no longer than 3 to 4 hours.
(May get soggy.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend milk and peanut butter together; add pudding and Dream Whip and mix on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into pie crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Swirl chocolate syrup on top and chopped peanuts.
Can use coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pasties
directions: Combine meat, potatoes and onions on 1/2 of the crust. Sprinkle with water, salt, pepper and margarine.
Fold uncovered portions of pastry over the mixture and crimp edges.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese real good.
Add flour, salt and Rice Krispies.
Roll dough into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies brown on the bottom.

title: cheddar cheese pineapple salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine gelatin and water.
Heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat in sour cream and mayonnaise. Stir in undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cheese.
Pour into a 4-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
To serve, unmold onto a lettuce-lined platter.
Serves 6.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix salt into unsifted flour.
Cut Crisco in flour with a flour blender
or
two
table
knives.
Put egg, vinegar and water in a small	jar
with
a lid and shake well to mix.
Add liquid mixture to	flour,	forming a ball.
Divide into 3 to 4 portions. Shape
each into a round slightly flattened "cake". Dough can be stored in individual bags indefinitely or frozen.

title: dessert rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon together until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of crumbs into 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Make sauce up of sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla. Cook until thick and clear and then pour over rhubarb and sprinkle with remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with milk or cold with whipped cream.
We prefer it cold.

title: christmas cookies
directions: In medium bowl cream together the sugar, oleo and eggs.
Set aside.
In separate bowl combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Then add fruit and nuts.
Drop by small teaspoon and bake for 15 minutes at 300°.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda, dissolved in hot water.
Add flour.
Place peanuts in plastic bag and crush with rolling pin.
Add peanuts and mix well. Form in three long rolls and wrap in plastic wrap.
Store in refrigerator several hours, then slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until light brown.

title: zucchini casserole italian
directions: Peel zucchini so some of skin is left on and slice.
Simmer until fairly done, 10 to 15 minutes.
In frypan, saute onion and green pepper.
Add flour.
Mix. Add tomatoes.
Also, add bay leaf. Put zucchini in bottom of casserole.
Put rest of recipe on top. Top with Parmesan.
Bake 20 minutes or so at 350°.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 35 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares, while still warm.
Makes 30 to 35 brownies, about 1 1/2-inches square.

title: peanut butter frozen pie
directions: Mix together with electric mixer and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze and then thaw enough to serve.
May be topped with Cool Whip.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Work dough thoroughly until it forms into a smooth ball.
For best results, spread grease on the dough.
Pinch off small balls of dough and roll it as if making a pie crust.
Roll real thin.
Put tortilla on a heated grill, a pancake grill or cast-iron skillet. Brown a little on each side.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pork loin
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicago style italian beef
directions: Mix spices together in a separate bowl.
Alternate layers of meat, sliced onions, peppers and spice mix.
Add water to half full.
Cook at 350° until tender.
Best to use an oblong Nesco cooker or covered roasting pan.

title: ratatouille
directions: Salt and drain eggplant on paper towel for 20 minutes.
Saute eggplant, zucchini, pepper and onions in olive oil until lightly browned.
Stir in tomato, salt, basil and pepper. Transfer to a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or cook on top of stove in heavy pot.
Top with cheese, bake another half hour.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Place ground beef in 2 qt. casserole.
Microwave at HIGH for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, or until beef is no longer pink, stirring once. Drain.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: First in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Second ingredient, blend a minute.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
One milk, 1 fruit, 16 optional.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Layer baking pan with 1 package crescent rolls.
Seal edges. Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread mixture over layer of rolls in pan.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain and add 1 cup water.
Then layer beef in bottom of a skillet.
Layer vegetables over beef.
Put rest of beef over vegetables and pour soup over all.
Lay cheese over top. Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Wash spinach and cook without adding water until tender; drain and chop.
Melt butter; blend in flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add spinach and heat well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
