title: pecan-cheese crispies
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with mixer until blended.
Add hot sauce and mustard; add flours, mixing well, then stir in cereal.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten with a fork.
Press a pecan half in the center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes; cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and put in can or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with finger.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Make pancakes.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potatoes.
Do not add any milk or butter.
Place potatoes on a board and knead in sugar, a little at a time until the texture of pie dough.
Roll out with rolling pin, about 1/8-inch thick. Spread jelly or peanut butter on top, then roll up into a roll. Refrigerate and then slice and enjoy.

title: marshmallow pops on a stick
directions: Place caramels, butter adn sweet milk in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until candy and butter melt and mixture is smooth. Pour cereal in a large bowl; set aside.

title: any way you like it pizza
directions: Mix water and yeast in a bowl.
Wait 5 minutes, then add flour.
Mix with floured hands.
Roll into a ball.
Cover and let rise, then punch down.
Let rise again.
On a floured board, roll out.
Put on pizza pan that has been oiled.
Next, put on spaghetti sauce, then cheese.
Top as desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crust is golden around edges.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly and add to first mixture.
Cook in boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove.
Add butter and vanilla and cool.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Boil soup.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and gelatin, stir. Add other ingredients and pour into a greased mold.
Chill.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika and set aside.
Brown garlic in oleo; add steak, onions and green peppers and continue cooking until vegetables are wilted.
Add tomatoes and broth; cover and simmer over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Blend water and cornstarch with soy sauce and stir into steak mixture; cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions thin and saute in butter (enough butter to make them limp).
Add onion soup mix and water as called for in directions.
Cook until onions are done, about 30 minutes.
Cut day old French bread into pieces.
Put in onion mix.
Add grated Gruyere cheese.
Cook at about 400° in oven until cheese is melted. Don't overcook cheese.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and crumble potatoes into a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Butter bottom and sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until warm.

title: jiffy nutmeg cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour four 7 1/4-inch pans (there's no need to bake all batter at once).
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and nutmeg in large bowl.
Add cream, eggs and rum; beat with electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute, or until well blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 3 minutes longer, until thick.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; let cool completely.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 2/3 cup margarine.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and press in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Beat remaining margarine with eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas; dip in pineapple juice and arrange on egg mixture.
Place pineapple on top of bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup; sprinkle chopped nuts and maraschino cherries over top.
Chill for 8 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Beat egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in sugars.
Add biscuit mix and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: soft chipper cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Blend margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in half of the flour mixture. Add buttermilk and remaining flour mixture. Add chips and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: pink pudding
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add syrup, water and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in rice, fruit and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: moon cookies
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks, margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add flour and baking powder and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Fold in unbeaten egg whites, gently, until mixture is smooth.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle with ground nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut with glass, making circles that overlap one another to make moons.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.	Cut in 1/4-inch pieces and put in heavy boiler.
Add chopped onions and peppers and remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling
point and let simmer for three hours, stirring often.
Seal in jars.

title: christmas molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Blend in orange juice, corn syrup and molasses.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Roll dough, a portion at a time, on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 2-inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and chewy if baked 12 minutes or crunchy if baked longer. Makes 6 to 7 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Debone chicken. Melt butter and chop onion.
Combine and saute.
Add soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cut up cheese and add to mixture.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Put in oven, uncovered, until it bubbles.
Bake at 375°.

title: crockpot chili
directions: Put beans in crock pot while you brown hamburger.
Add hamburger to beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low all day.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Soak chicken in eggs overnight.
Roll chicken in Ritz crackers and brown in oil.
Place in pan.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Cover with mushrooms and squeeze lemon over chicken.
Mix wine and chicken broth.
Pour over. Place cheese. Cover with foil. Leave corner of foil turned back.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: silver white cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk, shortening and vanilla in large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 2 minutes.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Let cool.
Frost with White Mountain Frosting.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine, oil and egg.
Mix together with all the other ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients except bacon; pour into casserole dish. Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Dissolve orange, cherry and lime jello each with 1 cup water. Dissolve lemon jello with pineapple juice.
Mash all of this jello up together.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter and powdered sugar.
If dry, sprinkle with milk.
Roll into balls about the size of quarters. Chill about an hour.
Mix chocolate chips and approximately 1/2 pound of paraffin, which has been melted in a double boiler.
Dip balls in this mixture and place on wax paper to set.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Put ingredients in 9-inch square pan in the order listed.
Mix until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken, shrimp or crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips; put in casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° until hot, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Put 1 cup pecans in bottom
of pie shell.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and buttermilk.
Pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake until firm in the middle and brown on top.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and freeze all ingredients.
Take out of freezer the night before serving and place in refrigerator.
Mash with potato masher to make slush before serving.
Wonderful on a hot summer day.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt together over low flame, peanut butter and margarine. Combine graham cracker crumbs and confectioners sugar with first mixture.
Press into small cupcake liners.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spoon melted chocolate over peanut butter cups. Refrigerate to set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Using 3-quart pan, cook together first three ingredients until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown. Remove from stove and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Beat real fast and pour into very large buttered surface.

title: apple crisp cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons of butter and 1 cup of oats; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg; mix until well blended.
Press into greased pan. Pour pie filling over crust and spread.
To reserved crumbs, add 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons butter, nuts and brown sugar.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve baking soda in milk; add vanilla.
Add this to the first mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet or add enough flour to make cutouts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Put three cans of beans in a greased casserole dish.
In separate bowl mix Miracle Whip, oil, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Combine with beans and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until onion rings are brown.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and vegetables to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add kielbasa and soup; heat through.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and black bean bake
directions: In a shallow 2 to 2 1/2-quart baking dish, stir together bean mix, boiling water and sherry (use larger amount if you prefer a sauce-like consistency).
Lay chicken breasts slightly apart on the beans.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven until chicken is no longer pink in center of thickest part (cut to test), about 20 minutes.
Stir any excess liquid around the chicken into the beans.
Mound shredded lettuce on 4 dinner plates; top with equal portions of beans and chicken. Sprinkle with shredded Jack cheese and sliced chili and garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Offer yogurt to add to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Pour in an iron skillet and cook until it gets thick.
When this gets done, have your pie shell cooked and ready to pour the
mixture in.
Just after it gets thick, add butter and vanilla.
Pour in the pie shell.
Let chill for a little bit and then it is ready to eat.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in own juice until hot.
Pour off juice and save.
Mash until smooth.
Combine butter and milk; beat, then add brown sugar.
Add salt and cinnamon; beat until smooth.
Pour into pan placing marshmallows on top and reheat.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Cook hamburger on top of stove and chop with fork until crumbly. When done, drain oil and set aside.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients to mix well.
Add water and oil; beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and beat 1 to 2 minutes until mixed well.
Add chocolate chips; stir in with a spoon until mixed in well.
Bake in floured and greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°. Cool 10 minutes.
Great with Cool Whip, ice cream, etc.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole over stove.
Place blintzes in casserole.
Blend all other ingredients with well beaten eggs. Pour liquid over blintzes in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top browns.
Serve with powdered sugar or strawberries.

title: summer garden marinade
directions: Place vegetables in a covered bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over veggies.
Cover and let marinate at least several hours in the refrigerator.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown stew meat.
Boil meat, bouillon cubes, water and beef broth for 30 minutes.
Add frozen egg noodles.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
If desired, you can thicken with cornstarch.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine everything and save 1/4 cup grated cheese for top. Put in pie plate.
Put grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not freeze.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; cool and slice.
Boil soup, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over carrots.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken with sweet sour sauce
directions: Skin chicken.
Season chicken with garlic salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
Dip in beaten egg.
Chill for 1/2 hour so coating will adhere.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Simmer to brown.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift together and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Start in a cold oven.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender.
Stir occasionally to separate into rings.
Drain well.
Place 1/2 of onions into 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the toast.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir milk.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper and hot mixture to beaten eggs, a little at a time, until blended.
Add another layer of onions, cheese and toast.
Pour sauce over top.
Lift to let sauce get down through. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk and boil to soft ball stage, stirring continuously. Remove from heat and add marshmallow creme and chocolate chips. Stir until smooth. Pour into greased 9 X 13 pan. May add nuts if desired.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour, cake mix and salt. Add water.
Mix well.
Knead.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and make out rolls.
Let rise in a greased pan for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on top.
Brush tops with butter.

title: easy rice pudding(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart casserole combine all ingredients.
Microwave on High for five minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool for five minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Chill.
Serves 4.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash and pack small, whole cukes in quart loosely. Add the next 4 ingredients.
Finish jar with cold water.
Let stand at least 1 month, then open as needed.
Pour off vinegar, slice, add 2 cups sugar and enough water to dissolve sugar and fill jar.
Let stand 24 hours before eating.
Shake jar while in refrigerator when you are in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and chill about 2 hours.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Combine chicken, soup, sour cream and milk in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: coconut cream dressing
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: chicken 'n dressing
directions: Mix soup and water with a whisk and put into a greased casserole baking dish.
Lay chicken bone side down into soup mixture.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions.
Place prepared stuffing on top of chicken breasts. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until done, when chicken is no longer pink.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Empty Cheddar cheese soup cans into pan on stove top.
Stir in soup cans filled with milk on medium heat.
After lumps are gone, stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook for 1/2 hour over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Can be served over baked potato, toasted bread or in a bowl.

title: bread and butter pickle
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Cover with ice and salt.
Chill for 3 hours.
Mix together sugar, turmeric, pickling spice, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and let come to a boiling point, but do not boil.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal tightly.

title: portuguese sopas
directions: Cook beef in 2 quarts water at a low boil for about 1/2 hour periodically, skimming foam off the top.
When all foam is removed, add spices (except salt), Worcestershire sauce, wine, catsup, tomato paste, tomato sauce and onions.
Simmer over low heat for 3 hours until meat is almost done and broth is thick. Add salt and cabbage and simmer until cooked through for about an hour.
Remove stew from heat; cool slightly.
Serve in a large bowl, pouring stew over pieces of sliced, day-old French bread that has been toasted slightly.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: breakfast casserole(serving size: 8)
directions: Put bread in a greased casserole.
Brown and drain sausage. Sprinkle over bread.
Add cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and dry ingredients.
Pour over bread mixture; refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Lightly salt the chicken and place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake for 30 more minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil without stirring to soft ball stage (234°) or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water, forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool then beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread into pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Hand blend well; it will be thick. Spread in floured and Pam-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: country-fried potatoes
directions: In large heavy skillet, fry bacon. Remove bacon and crumble. In bacon drippings, cook potatoes, onion and pepper. Season to taste and cook over low fire until potatoes are browned. Add in bacon and stir.

title: baked chicken breasts a la russe
directions: Wipe chicken dry on both sides with paper toweling.
Combine sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, liquid red pepper, garlic, salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Place chicken in close fitting, shallow glass baking dish.
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken. Marinate, covered, overnight.
Turn chicken occasionally during marinating period.
Leaving as much marinade on chicken pieces as possible, dip each piece into bread crumbs to coat.
Shape chicken pieces into compact bundles (but don't fold them).
Place chicken in single layer in ungreased baking dish.
Refrigerate again, covered for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Place chicken in oven directly from refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, in oven preheated to 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with Baked Rice Pilaf.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Let the pineapple and marshmallows stand overnight in a large bowl.
Next morning fold in whipped cream and top with nuts. Chill until needed.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour 2 tablespoons of oil in a 13 x 9-inch pan until evenly coated.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Blend the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed. Blend in the eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips. Pour batter into the crust. Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup mini chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.

title: triple fudge chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add dry pudding mix.
Pour batter into baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts generously on top of batter.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: wonderful divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, hot water and salt in saucepan, stirring to dissolve sugar entirely.
Cover pan and cook five minutes.
Uncover pan and continue cooking to hard, but not brittle, stage.
Remove from heat.

Beat egg whites until just foamy, then start adding hot syrup in a pencil-thin stream, beating constantly, using rotary beater or electric mixer. Continue beating for three to five minutes until candy thickens and loses its gloss.
Remove from beater and stir in vanilla, fruit or nuts.
Drop quickly by tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Let set one hour.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Sift flour and cocoa; mix well with coconut and pecans.
Mix with melted oleo, then add sugar, eggs and vanilla mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 3 pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Immediately spread jar of marshmallow cream over the top.
Let set 30 minutes, then frost.

title: maureen's beans
directions: Drain beans and mix in pot.
Saute hamburger, bacon and onion and drain.
Chop bacon.
Mix remaining ingredients and combine all in pot.
Slow cook for 3 to 5 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets well.
Leave 2 inches of the stem and tap root. Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain beet juice into another pan.
Strain juice several times with cloth.
Put cold water on beets and let cool down.
Skin will slip off easy.
Trim stems and roots off.
Large beets can be quartered or sliced, small beets can be left whole.
Mix sugar, vinegar and beet juice and bring to a boil.
Pack beets in hot jars and add pickling spice. Pour hot juice over beets and seal.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix together and add corn; mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
In 9 x 12-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam, pour in mixture.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine and sugar, stir until dissolved.
Add dates and water.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add next three ingredients.
Remove from heat and stir in the Rice Krispies. Cool enough that you can handle mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls while warm.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar at a time with shortening.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine salt and flour.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Blend in vanilla and food coloring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: madison's cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin puree and oil. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add cranberries and mix. Divide dough into 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans. Bake 50 minutes.

title: lemon meringue torte
directions: Mix flour and sugar and set aside.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Separate eggs.
Egg yolks should be about 1/2 cup and whites about 3/4 cup.
Add egg yolks to butter.
Add flour and sugar to creamed mixture.
Add lemon juice and milk; mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry (they form a peak) and fold into the custard mix with a wire whip.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set in a pan of warm water and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Chill and serve with whipped cream topping, if desired.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together and add sugar to taste.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat chili beans and drain.
Mash beans or put in food processor or blender.
Add cheese.
Blend well and heat again on low or in microwave.
Serve with corn chips or as a spread for corn bread.

title: ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise over 1 side of bread.
Repeat with other slice.
Place ham on one side and the cheese on the other.
Put together with cheese on top.
Put paper towel under sandwich.
Heat on High for 35 to 50 seconds.
Let cool for 1 minute.

title: crab-asparagus pate
directions: Drain asparagus; puree in blender.
Soften gelatin using the 2 tablespoons liquid and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Heat soup and cheese together over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; heat until gelatin melts.
Put in mold. (Entire mixture fits in a 2-quart mold or can be broken down into smaller ones.)
Enjoy!

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix ingredients well; spread over pie crust.
Place fruit (such as strawberries, kiwi, bananas, etc.) over cheese mixture. Chill.
Very pretty!

title: cheese cake
directions: Crumb together margarine and cracker crumbs and bake 8 minutes at 350°; cool.
Combine sugar and cream cheese.
Prepare Dream Whip, then combine with cheese mixture and spread on top of crumbs and put in refrigerator.

title: english pork pies
directions: Make crust day before by combining first 4 ingredients.
Cut pork into small pieces (walnut size).
Soak meat in seasoned water overnight.
Next day make into 2 crusts pies (individual or regular).
Bake for 1 hour at 450° or 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Take from oven; cut hole in center of pie.
Then pour into pie 1 envelope Knox gelatine dissolved in 1 pint of water.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening.
Blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix batter until smooth and well blended. Takes about 1 minute.
Add chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet, placing cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: bubba's hot dish
directions: Heat everything together for about 5 minutes (until noodles are no longer stiff).
Mix and bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes, covered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping. Blend well. Spoon into crust. Chill until set (at least 4 hours). Garnish with cherries. Prep time: 15 minutes.

title: "hot air" marshmallow strawberry dessert
directions: In a double boiler dissolve marshmallows in milk.
Cool. Blend in whipped cream and strawberries.
Crush graham crackers and layer in bottom of large flat glass dish.
Pour strawberry/marshmallow mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with crushed graham crackers.
Chill.
Slice and serve with a spatula.

title: summer vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: gourmet club sandwich
directions: Remove crusts from bread and place 6 slices in oblong buttered ovenproof dish.
Beat together eggs, mustard, milk, Accent and seasoned salt.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl, adding 7-Up last.
Add drops of red food coloring as desired (optional).
Stir.
Add ice, orange and lemon slices.

title: john's chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain grease if using ground beef.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add all other ingredients, breaking up all tomatoes.
Mix well and bring to a simmer. Simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour and covered for 1 1/2 hours (the longer the better).
Serves 6.

title: 2 quick pastas
directions: No. 2:
Change olive oil to butter.
Add shredded Mozzarella or Monterey Jack cheese.
Add heavy cream (optional).

title: instant amaretto cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in airtight container.
To serve, place 3 heaping tablespoons mix in mug; add very hot water and stir.
Enjoy!

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour to make it stiff enough to roll.
Roll out and let dry.
Cut into strips and cook 20 minutes in chicken broth.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, chicken broth, onion, seasonings, chicken and bread crumbs; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch).
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.
Invert loaf onto platter.
Serve with almond mushroom sauce.
Slice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can double.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix the water, honey, lecithin and vitamin C.
Add flours. Mix and knead until it's a firm, soft dough.
Let rest for about 1/2 hour.
Punch down and form into 1 loaf.
Put in a loaf pan. Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef with onions, green pepper, salt and pepper. Drain off fat.
Add to beans and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Stir before using.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water with lemon juice.
Chill but do not let set.
Chill until icy the can of milk (may be chilled in
ice tray).
Soften
cream
cheese
(if	using an electric mixer,
milk and
cream
cheese
may be mixed together).
Add sugar,
when beaten
until
stiff;
add	vanilla.
Add
jello mixture.
Roll crackers
fine, mix oleo and sugar.
Line pan. Keep back about 1/3 of the mixture to sprinkle on top.

title: chicken with drop dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done. Remove chicken from broth. Mix all other ingredients together. Drop by tablespoons for large, or teaspoons for small, dumplings into simmering broth.
Cook until dumplings are done. De-bone chicken and add to broth.

title: secret recipe chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
Place rolled oats in blender of food processor and process until finely ground.
Combine ground oats, flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Mix crumbs with cheese and roll chicken in it.
Put into buttered dish; dot with butter, oil and garlic salt.
(Drizzle oil on very slowly, using teaspoon.)
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn and put more butter on each breast (use 1 thin pat, cut into thirds for each piece).
Cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more, or until browns nicely.
Serves 4.

title: potato kabobs with cheese sauce
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Cut each half crosswise into four pieces.
On 6 to 10-inch skewers, thread potatoes.
Brush potatoes with oil.
On grill rack, arrange kabobs directly above medium coals.
Grill uncovered 30 minutes or until fork tender, turning once during cooking.
In 1 quart saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir the cream cheese until slightly softened.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except walnuts and paprika.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: creole chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
In large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Stir in soup, water and ketchup.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: wine cake
directions: May add 1/2 cup each chopped nuts, raisins and/or candied cherries to yellow cake.
Bourbon may be used in place of wine. Add Macadamia nuts and drained pineapple bits.
Best with glaze and improves with age!

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Spray Pam in a 9x12 baking dish.
Fill the dish with sliced yellow squash.
Pour enough milk to cover the bottom of the dish. Sprinkle Tony Chachere's creole seasoning to cover the top. Sprinkle green onions on top.
Cover with foil and bake in 350 degree oven 1 hour, until squash is soft.
Remove and mash.
Stir in brown sugar and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and bake about 15 minutes or so.
Serves lots!

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter in a small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Blend remaining butter with cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup of the sugar, beating well.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Peel or scrape carrots; grate or put through blender.
Combine with raisins, salt and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheez whiz
directions: Cut cheese and melt in double boiler.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Return to heat; stir and cook until eggs thicken slightly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slowly and stir.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: While boiling, add:
2 eggs or Egg Beaters, beaten with a whip and combined with 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Drop into boiling soup, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Add meatballs and simmer.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook all day on low in crock-pot.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and oleo; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over completely cooled crust. Mix instant vanilla pudding and milk according to directions on package; spread evenly over second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cook noodles, sunflower kernels, pecans and butter until brown. Mix together the coleslaw and green onions, then add Ramen noodles mixture.
Mix other ingredients.
Stir all together.

title: parmesan fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Put shortening in oblong 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan and set in oven to melt. Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken at a time in bag. Coat thoroughly.
Place chicken, skin side down, in hot shortening.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 of the flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
(I use my temperature probe of my microwave for this.
It works great!)
Gradually add milk mixture to dry mixture and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.

title: aunt marty's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift cocoa, flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk; mix well. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done in 8 or 9-inch square pan. Let cool and frost (frost and serve in pan).

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in bowl or jello mold and chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple squares
directions: Toss apples, sugar and spices together.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla and add to apples.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saucy steak
directions: Cook beef in olive oil for 2 minutes on each side.
Place on side dish. Cover and keep warm.
Put bouillon and small amount of water into same pan.
Let liquids cook down (glaze).
Add all vegetables.
Let cook on low heat until done. Sauce should be semi-thick.
Put steaks back in and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together
and sprinkle cornflakes over top with 1/2 stick melted butter
or
margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smoked spiced wild turkey
directions: You will need a smoker.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together on low speed.
Add eggs, one by one, beating continuously.
Then add flour and milk.
Continue mixing until nice and smooth.
Add flavor.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Frost with white frosting mixed with coconut after cooling completely.

title: spicy corn relish
directions: Cook corn in boiling
water
for 3 minutes.
Remove and cool. Cut kernels from cobs.
Put peppers, cabbage and onions through food chopper,
using
coarse
blade.
In
large
heavy kettle blend salt,
sugar,
flour, turmeric and mustard.
Stir in vinegar, slowly.
Bring mixture to boil and add vegetables. Reduce heat and simmer
25 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and
seal
at
once.
Process
in
boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Store in cool, dark place.
Yields about 12 pints.

title: chess pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix
flour
and sugar, then other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until done.

title: holiday cut-outs(cookies)
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan coated with cooking spray, in a layer about 1/2-inch thick.
When slightly cooled, use holiday cookie cutter to cut into shapes.
Decorate as desired with prepared frosting and candies.
Yields 9 (3 1/4-inch) cut-outs.

title: sweet sour dressing for 50
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add to shredded cabbage 30 minutes before serving.
Makes enough for 50 people.

title: chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato, beans, chili powder, basil and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: sour cream and nut pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together 2 times.
Cream butter. Slowly add sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well in between.
Stir in sour cream.
Add dry ingredients, 1/2 cup at a time, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or separate into 2 smaller loaves. Bake at 325° for at least 1 hour, without opening oven door.

title: lime cream pie
directions: In bowl, stir together condensed milk and lime juice (use food coloring if desired for more color).
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set, keep frozen for several days.

title: dressing for lettuce
directions: Mix sugar, mustard seed, salt, onion and one-half of the vinegar.
Beat and add oil.
Beat remainder of vinegar and add celery seed.
(I mix in blender.)
Can be stored in jar in refrigerator for future use.

title: sugar crisp rolls(elephant ears)
directions: Scald 1/4 cup milk.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve 1 package active dry east in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add milk mixture, egg, 1 cup flour and beat until smooth.
Add about 1 1/4 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top; cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down, let rise again about 1/2 hour.
Roll out to a 9 x 18-inch oblong.
Brush with melted margarine.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Mix egg whites, salt and pepper.
Dip onions in mixture, then dip onion in bread crumbs.
Place in single layers on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: basic southern fried quail
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Dip quail in water and shake off excess.
Drop quail into bag and shake, covering each bird thoroughly.
Heat a frying pan half filled with oil.
Brown quail on both sides.
Cover skillet and reduce heat. Cook slowly until tender, about 30 minutes, turning once to brown evenly.

title: roadside potato bread
directions: Cook milk, sugar, lard or oleo, salt and instant potatoes until all mixed together.
Let set until lukewarm, then add 2 to 3 cups of flour and yeast.
Start sifting 10 to 11 cups of flour. Knead.
Let set until doubled in size, then poke it down.
Let raise again.
Put in bread pans and then let raise again.
Put in oven and bake until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook peeled and cubed zucchini in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine all ingredients in 10 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: saucy burgers
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, in medium bowl, mix well the ground beef, 1/2 cup marinara sauce, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook patties until well browned on both sides. Drain on paper towels.
Pour drippings from skillet. Return meat to skillet and pour remaining sauce over meat. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple-pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: rudolph's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup mayonnaise, dash of sugar and 2 tablespoons of water.
Mix and top salad.

title: texas lemon pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pan of water on lower rack to keep cake from drying out.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and lemon extract. Mix well; add pecans.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans. (Divide batter into 2 Bundt pans.)
Cake usually has a crack on top.
After about 30 minutes, place a brown paper (cut from paper bag) over the cake.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Time may vary with each stove.
Let cool for a few minutes before removing from pans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure; add soda, baking powder and salt. Sift again. Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually add the sugars and cream thoroughly. Add the well beaten egg. Combine the dry ingredients and creamed mixture.

Chill. Form into balls, 1 inch in diameter and place on a lightly greased and floured baking sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in flour. Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: ramen broccoli slaw
directions: Mix together broccoli slaw, noodles (broken into small pieces), almonds, sunflower seeds, green onions and seasoning from noodles; set aside until ready to serve.
